1
00:00:02,329 --> 00:00:06,249
[HEAVY DRAMATIC MUSIC]

2
00:00:27,979 --> 00:00:32,067
Many years ago, in
the realm of Apollyon,

3
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:34,444
past the garden
of four rivers,

4
00:00:34,444 --> 00:00:37,197
and in the region of Abaddan,

5
00:00:37,197 --> 00:00:41,201
there stood an old city.

6
00:00:41,201 --> 00:00:45,455
Its name in the ancient
tongue was Noit Curtsed.

7
00:00:45,455 --> 00:00:48,875
But time and speech
and a brilliant mind

8
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:50,877
named Lux soon set upon the

9
00:00:50,877 --> 00:00:55,132
more pleasant name
of Not Cursed.

10
00:00:55,132 --> 00:00:58,343
Though some would have
thought it wishful thinking,

11
00:00:58,343 --> 00:01:02,847
for the city was indeed
cursed with perpetual decay,

12
00:01:02,847 --> 00:01:05,558
leaving the
inhabitants no choice

13
00:01:05,558 --> 00:01:07,977
but to labor perpetually

14
00:01:07,977 --> 00:01:12,064
for the very sake
of their existence.

15
00:01:12,064 --> 00:01:16,068
Years, decades, and centuries
passed, and the city

16
00:01:16,068 --> 00:01:19,239
grew in number and labor.

17
00:01:19,239 --> 00:01:22,074
Ruling over it were
the Supervisors,

18
00:01:22,074 --> 00:01:23,368
descendants of Lux.

19
00:01:26,329 --> 00:01:29,749
Brilliant organizers, they
kept the city in existence

20
00:01:29,749 --> 00:01:33,461
by the oversight of endless
shifts and schedules.

21
00:01:33,461 --> 00:01:35,087
Obstinate Heady.

22
00:01:35,087 --> 00:01:36,589
Next.

23
00:01:36,589 --> 00:01:38,466
Christian Pilgrim.

24
00:01:38,466 --> 00:01:39,592
Next.

25
00:01:39,592 --> 00:01:40,968
[CHRISTIAN SIGHS]

26
00:01:40,968 --> 00:01:41,969
[GASP]

27
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:43,388
Oh!

28
00:01:43,388 --> 00:01:47,475
Work was paramount, which is
why such a commotion resulted

29
00:01:47,475 --> 00:01:51,354
one day when it was
discovered that--

30
00:01:51,354 --> 00:01:53,481
A man has gone missing!

31
00:01:56,108 --> 00:01:59,321
What?

32
00:01:59,321 --> 00:02:00,447
Stand back, now.

33
00:02:00,447 --> 00:02:01,448
[THUD]

34
00:02:01,448 --> 00:02:02,949
Once more and--

35
00:02:02,949 --> 00:02:03,950
[CRASH]

36
00:02:06,453 --> 00:02:09,456
[SOFT MUSIC]

37
00:02:09,456 --> 00:02:11,624
Whoa.

38
00:02:11,624 --> 00:02:13,501
Oh, my.

39
00:02:19,591 --> 00:02:21,968
Tear it all down, and burn it.

40
00:02:21,968 --> 00:02:23,470
All of it.

41
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,637
Hurry up, now.

42
00:02:24,637 --> 00:02:27,724
Supervisor 6 will
be here any minute.

43
00:02:27,724 --> 00:02:31,436
And I'd be very
careful if I were you.

44
00:02:31,436 --> 00:02:35,815
You want to avoid
any contamination.

45
00:02:35,815 --> 00:02:40,320
[SOFT MUSIC]

46
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:43,698
So, that's him.

47
00:02:43,698 --> 00:02:45,617
Right, you are.

48
00:02:45,617 --> 00:02:48,828
Faithful Pathfinder.

49
00:02:48,828 --> 00:02:51,122
Yeesh.

50
00:02:52,457 --> 00:02:55,335
What a madman.

51
00:02:55,335 --> 00:02:57,712
[SOFT MUSIC]

52
00:03:01,466 --> 00:03:02,467
[CHRISTIAN SIGHS]

53
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:06,721
Well, you can't really
blame a man for dreaming,

54
00:03:06,721 --> 00:03:08,890
can you, Obstinate?

55
00:03:08,890 --> 00:03:11,351
Even if he is a madman.

56
00:03:11,351 --> 00:03:13,060
Was a madman.

57
00:03:17,189 --> 00:03:19,066
Only a madman would
be foolish enough

58
00:03:19,066 --> 00:03:21,694
to venture beyond the borders.

59
00:03:21,694 --> 00:03:24,364
Nothing good ever comes
from veering from the rules,

60
00:03:24,364 --> 00:03:25,072
I always say.

61
00:03:25,072 --> 00:03:26,574
Nothing at all.

62
00:03:29,827 --> 00:03:31,496
Beyond the borders?

63
00:03:31,496 --> 00:03:33,205
Is that where he went?

64
00:03:33,205 --> 00:03:34,749
Yes.

65
00:03:34,749 --> 00:03:36,208
And everyone knows
there's nothing

66
00:03:36,208 --> 00:03:39,254
but death beyond the borders.

67
00:03:39,254 --> 00:03:41,088
Isn't that right, uh--

68
00:03:41,088 --> 00:03:42,840
what is your name?

69
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,384
Christian, Supervisor.

70
00:03:44,384 --> 00:03:45,718
I mean, Christian.

71
00:03:45,718 --> 00:03:48,471
You're the
supervisor, obviously.

72
00:03:48,471 --> 00:03:50,598
And you don't want to catch
the same thing Faithful

73
00:03:50,598 --> 00:03:52,350
Pathfinder did, do you?

74
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:57,104
Whatever it is that drove
him to this deviation.

75
00:03:57,104 --> 00:03:57,689
No.

76
00:03:57,689 --> 00:03:58,815
No, surely not.

77
00:03:58,815 --> 00:03:59,566
Of course not.

78
00:03:59,566 --> 00:04:00,066
Never.

79
00:04:00,066 --> 00:04:00,567
No.

80
00:04:00,567 --> 00:04:02,735
Good.

81
00:04:02,735 --> 00:04:05,697
Do not fail to collect
every last scrap of paper.

82
00:04:05,697 --> 00:04:08,950
Every sketch, any notes.

83
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:10,702
And you.

84
00:04:10,702 --> 00:04:12,954
Yes, my superior?

85
00:04:12,954 --> 00:04:14,956
I have a task for you.

86
00:04:14,956 --> 00:04:16,874
Right away, my superior.

87
00:04:16,874 --> 00:04:18,876
[LAUGH]

88
00:04:19,877 --> 00:04:23,381
[GENTLE MUSIC]

89
00:05:06,257 --> 00:05:08,760
[INSECTS CHIRPING]

90
00:05:12,764 --> 00:05:14,223
[WHOOSHING]

91
00:05:14,223 --> 00:05:15,725
[EXPLOSION]

92
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:18,686
[GASPING]

93
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:30,698
[SOFT MUSIC]

94
00:05:34,702 --> 00:05:36,203
[DOOR CREAKS]

95
00:05:51,093 --> 00:05:56,098
What was Faithful Pathfinder
thinking, I wonder?

96
00:06:00,937 --> 00:06:05,942
It has been said that no
one just finds the Book,

97
00:06:07,068 --> 00:06:11,864
but, rather, the
Book finds them.

98
00:06:11,864 --> 00:06:15,201
And so it happened that
Christian began to read.

99
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:21,207
And read.

100
00:06:21,207 --> 00:06:23,585
And read.

101
00:06:23,585 --> 00:06:26,337
And read.

102
00:06:26,337 --> 00:06:29,215
Unable to pry himself
from its pages,

103
00:06:29,215 --> 00:06:33,970
he read the Book all through
the night and all the next day

104
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:36,097
and the day after that.

105
00:06:36,097 --> 00:06:39,934
And the more he read, the
more his concern for right

106
00:06:39,934 --> 00:06:43,104
things grew until they
became, as it were,

107
00:06:43,104 --> 00:06:46,065
a great burden to him.

108
00:06:46,483 --> 00:06:50,570
Christian read about things
he had never imagined,

109
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:54,115
about kindnesses he had
never known existed,

110
00:06:54,115 --> 00:06:57,494
about wrongful things that
needed to be put right,

111
00:06:57,494 --> 00:07:01,372
about the origins of his
city, and about a coming--

112
00:07:02,749 --> 00:07:04,208
War?!

113
00:07:05,209 --> 00:07:08,129
We have to get
out, Christiana.

114
00:07:08,129 --> 00:07:13,092
It says so in this, and
I believe it in here.

115
00:07:13,092 --> 00:07:15,637
And the war will
destroy the entire city?

116
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,934
So we must flee
and get to the--

117
00:07:21,934 --> 00:07:25,688
Celestial City,
the City of Light.

118
00:07:25,688 --> 00:07:28,190
The City of--

119
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:30,693
[LAUGH]

120
00:07:34,071 --> 00:07:35,823
It's a book, Christian.

121
00:07:35,823 --> 00:07:39,577
If you'd only read it,
you would understand.

122
00:07:39,577 --> 00:07:41,579
It all makes-- [GROANS]

123
00:07:42,371 --> 00:07:44,331
Sense?

124
00:07:44,331 --> 00:07:46,125
You're asking me
and the children

125
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:50,379
to follow you
beyond the borders?

126
00:07:50,379 --> 00:07:51,338
[SOB]

127
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,383
No, Christian.

128
00:07:54,383 --> 00:07:56,093
It doesn't make sense.

129
00:07:56,093 --> 00:07:58,262
None at all.

130
00:07:58,262 --> 00:08:00,515
Ever since you started reading
that Book a few days ago,

131
00:08:00,515 --> 00:08:02,684
you have gone on and on
and on like some lunatic.

132
00:08:02,684 --> 00:08:04,811
"The city is going to be
destroyed. The city is

133
00:08:04,811 --> 00:08:06,854
going up in flames."

134
00:08:06,854 --> 00:08:08,314
It's hard for me
and for the children

135
00:08:08,314 --> 00:08:09,481
to see you in
this sorry state,

136
00:08:09,481 --> 00:08:11,317
all bent over and--

137
00:08:11,317 --> 00:08:14,236
It's this weight.

138
00:08:14,946 --> 00:08:15,697
Weight?

139
00:08:15,697 --> 00:08:18,199
What weight, Christian?

140
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:20,827
You've gone to nothing
but skin and bones.

141
00:08:20,827 --> 00:08:25,122
The more I read, the
more it weighs on me.

142
00:08:25,122 --> 00:08:26,708
Don't you see?

143
00:08:29,085 --> 00:08:31,337
Oh, Christian.

144
00:08:31,337 --> 00:08:33,464
I know.

145
00:08:33,464 --> 00:08:34,966
This all seems crazy.

146
00:08:34,966 --> 00:08:36,258
I do.

147
00:08:36,258 --> 00:08:37,594
But I love you.

148
00:08:37,594 --> 00:08:42,348
And--and I only want what
is best for us all.

149
00:08:42,348 --> 00:08:44,058
If the city is destroyed--

150
00:08:44,058 --> 00:08:46,185
Oh.

151
00:08:46,185 --> 00:08:48,855
If the city is
destroyed, I don't

152
00:08:48,855 --> 00:08:51,816
want you, the children,
or anyone else

153
00:08:51,816 --> 00:08:54,819
for that matter
to perish with it.

154
00:08:54,819 --> 00:08:58,197
I love you, Christiana.

155
00:08:58,197 --> 00:09:01,200
[SOFT MUSIC]

156
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,369
Then, choose.

157
00:09:03,369 --> 00:09:05,329
What?

158
00:09:05,329 --> 00:09:07,248
Choose, Christian.

159
00:09:07,248 --> 00:09:12,378
The children, I, we can't take
seeing you like this day in

160
00:09:12,378 --> 00:09:14,088
and day out.

161
00:09:14,088 --> 00:09:16,257
You're going to have to
choose what you want to do.

162
00:09:16,257 --> 00:09:19,594
Stay here with us or leave.

163
00:09:19,594 --> 00:09:21,345
Because we're not
going with you.

164
00:09:21,345 --> 00:09:22,597
We're not.

165
00:09:24,223 --> 00:09:25,725
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

166
00:09:25,725 --> 00:09:27,184
[DOOR SHUTS]

167
00:09:31,689 --> 00:09:35,192
[GENTLE MUSIC]

168
00:09:39,614 --> 00:09:40,572
[SIGH]

169
00:09:40,572 --> 00:09:43,075
[FOOTSTEPS]

170
00:09:52,001 --> 00:09:54,086
My superior.

171
00:09:54,086 --> 00:09:55,337
Any signs?

172
00:09:55,337 --> 00:09:56,088
Signs?

173
00:09:56,088 --> 00:09:57,089
Oh, lots.

174
00:09:57,089 --> 00:09:58,966
Why, there's one
right here, you see.

175
00:10:01,636 --> 00:10:05,139
Of the missing man, you fool.

176
00:10:05,139 --> 00:10:05,640
Oh!

177
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:07,433
Oh, oh, yes, yes.

178
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:08,100
Of course.

179
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:12,604
Well, uh, yes and no.

180
00:10:12,604 --> 00:10:15,316
Yes and no?

181
00:10:15,316 --> 00:10:18,194
We followed his footsteps
beyond the borders,

182
00:10:18,194 --> 00:10:24,200
you see, to, um, to the
Swamp of Despondency.

183
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,327
So that's where he ended up.

184
00:10:26,327 --> 00:10:29,080
[LAUGHS] The swamp.

185
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:34,836
Well, that's where the, uh,
"no" part fits in, my--

186
00:10:34,836 --> 00:10:36,337
What do you mean?

187
00:10:36,337 --> 00:10:42,218
Well, you see, his footsteps,
they sort of led in and out

188
00:10:42,218 --> 00:10:48,725
of the swamp toward
the, uh, outer realms.

189
00:10:48,725 --> 00:10:53,688
It seems that
Faithful is alive.

190
00:10:53,688 --> 00:10:54,689
[GASP]

191
00:10:54,689 --> 00:10:58,067
[HEAVY MUSIC]

192
00:10:59,068 --> 00:11:01,070
Alive?

193
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:01,863
Oh, dear.

194
00:11:01,863 --> 00:11:02,363
Oh, dear.

195
00:11:02,363 --> 00:11:03,740
Oh, dear.

196
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:06,200
The Master won't
be happy, will he?

197
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:10,621
When I need to hear the
obvious, I shall let you know.

198
00:11:10,621 --> 00:11:12,206
Oh, right.

199
00:11:12,206 --> 00:11:12,707
Of course.

200
00:11:12,707 --> 00:11:13,958
Mmm.

201
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:17,211
We cannot afford to
lose any more fools,

202
00:11:17,211 --> 00:11:18,587
certainly not before the war.

203
00:11:18,587 --> 00:11:22,383
But the Master must be told.

204
00:11:22,383 --> 00:11:23,384
Return to the city.

205
00:11:23,384 --> 00:11:25,720
Spread a rumor that
something too horrible

206
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,889
to recount befell Faithful.

207
00:11:27,889 --> 00:11:30,224
The less you say, the
more their imagination

208
00:11:30,224 --> 00:11:31,433
will fill in the blanks.

209
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:32,727
Ah!

210
00:11:32,727 --> 00:11:34,061
Brilliant.

211
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:36,563
Yes, a brilliant plan.

212
00:11:36,563 --> 00:11:37,189
Go.

213
00:11:37,189 --> 00:11:39,066
I won't be long.

214
00:11:39,066 --> 00:11:40,818
Right away, my superior.

215
00:11:40,818 --> 00:11:42,569
Right away.

216
00:11:42,569 --> 00:11:46,073
[HEAVY MUSIC]

217
00:11:46,073 --> 00:11:48,075
[EERIE WHOOSHING]

218
00:11:58,085 --> 00:12:02,006
[GENTLE MUSIC]

219
00:12:24,862 --> 00:12:26,363
[GROWL]

220
00:12:26,363 --> 00:12:29,867
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

221
00:12:43,339 --> 00:12:44,340
Master?

222
00:12:46,884 --> 00:12:50,387
What is it?

223
00:12:50,387 --> 00:12:51,597
Master...

224
00:12:51,597 --> 00:12:57,311
I do not need to be
reminded of my position.

225
00:12:57,311 --> 00:13:00,189
Yes, of course.

226
00:13:00,189 --> 00:13:03,692
One of your subjects,
a man called Faithful,

227
00:13:03,692 --> 00:13:05,111
he has gone missing.

228
00:13:05,111 --> 00:13:07,571
Well, he hasn't really
gone missing since we know

229
00:13:07,571 --> 00:13:13,202
he's gone to the outer realms.

230
00:13:13,202 --> 00:13:15,371
I see.

231
00:13:15,371 --> 00:13:17,832
I knew you would be
understanding, Master.

232
00:13:17,832 --> 00:13:19,876
We do try our best to--

233
00:13:19,876 --> 00:13:21,377
[SCREAM]

234
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:31,387
What gives you the impression
that I am understanding?

235
00:13:31,387 --> 00:13:32,847
I-- I-- I--

236
00:13:32,847 --> 00:13:33,764
I-- I--

237
00:13:33,764 --> 00:13:35,474
Get out!

238
00:13:35,474 --> 00:13:39,311
It won't happen again,
Master, I can assure--

239
00:13:39,311 --> 00:13:42,189
Creature.

240
00:13:42,189 --> 00:13:44,316
Master?

241
00:13:44,316 --> 00:13:46,944
Be vigilant.

242
00:13:46,944 --> 00:13:51,949
One fool has a tendency
to engender another.

243
00:13:59,456 --> 00:14:00,958
[WHOOSHING]

244
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:09,884
[GENTLE MUSIC]

245
00:14:11,343 --> 00:14:14,346
What am I doing?

246
00:14:14,346 --> 00:14:17,599
All I have is this--this map.

247
00:14:17,599 --> 00:14:19,435
What if I don't get
back to the city in time

248
00:14:19,435 --> 00:14:20,436
to rescue them?

249
00:14:24,065 --> 00:14:25,191
What should I do?

250
00:14:28,319 --> 00:14:29,361
What should I do?

251
00:14:33,074 --> 00:14:35,451
I believe I can
answer that question.

252
00:14:38,204 --> 00:14:40,122
I didn't see you there.

253
00:14:40,122 --> 00:14:42,583
That's because I
just showed up.

254
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:45,377
My name is Evangelist.

255
00:14:47,213 --> 00:14:50,882
Now, "What should I
do?" you were asking.

256
00:14:50,882 --> 00:14:53,135
And I shall tell you.

257
00:14:53,135 --> 00:14:54,136
Flee.

258
00:14:54,136 --> 00:14:54,886
Flee?

259
00:14:54,886 --> 00:14:55,972
Don't hesitate.

260
00:14:55,972 --> 00:14:57,389
Don't waste time.

261
00:14:57,389 --> 00:14:59,266
Do what you know you must.

262
00:14:59,266 --> 00:15:00,684
You'll soon see
with your eyes

263
00:15:00,684 --> 00:15:02,561
what you believe
in your heart,

264
00:15:02,561 --> 00:15:06,190
and you'll get rid of
that thing on your back.

265
00:15:06,190 --> 00:15:07,984
You can see it?

266
00:15:07,984 --> 00:15:10,861
Well, of course, I can, and
I daresay a heavy and sickly

267
00:15:10,861 --> 00:15:11,695
burden it is.

268
00:15:11,695 --> 00:15:14,573
Oh, it seems to grow
more by the day.

269
00:15:14,573 --> 00:15:18,202
As your sorrows do, dear
lad, so does your burden.

270
00:15:18,202 --> 00:15:21,747
But you'll never get rid of it
on your own, I guarantee you.

271
00:15:21,747 --> 00:15:25,084
Now, do you see that
gate over there?

272
00:15:25,084 --> 00:15:26,585
[LIGHT MUSIC]

273
00:15:26,585 --> 00:15:27,461
Gate?

274
00:15:27,461 --> 00:15:28,629
Where?

275
00:15:28,629 --> 00:15:30,965
Come, come now.
Don't wipe away your tears.

276
00:15:30,965 --> 00:15:32,216
Look through them.

277
00:15:32,216 --> 00:15:35,344
Sometimes tears have a
way of bringing clarity.

278
00:15:35,344 --> 00:15:37,096
I still can't--

279
00:15:37,096 --> 00:15:39,348
Look past your sorrow,
good Christian.

280
00:15:39,348 --> 00:15:41,433
I-- oh.

281
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:43,685
Wait.

282
00:15:43,685 --> 00:15:45,479
I think I see it.

283
00:15:45,479 --> 00:15:47,064
There, I do.

284
00:15:47,064 --> 00:15:47,856
Near the light.

285
00:15:47,856 --> 00:15:48,440
Good.

286
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:48,940
Good.

287
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:50,859
Now, listen to me.

288
00:15:50,859 --> 00:15:54,571
Keep that light in your eye,
and go straight towards it.

289
00:15:54,571 --> 00:15:57,366
Do not turn to the
right or to the left.

290
00:15:57,366 --> 00:15:57,866
Keep--

291
00:15:57,866 --> 00:15:59,493
--on the straight path.

292
00:15:59,493 --> 00:16:00,452
Very good.

293
00:16:00,452 --> 00:16:03,122
Now, soon enough, you
will come to the gate.

294
00:16:03,122 --> 00:16:03,955
The gate.

295
00:16:03,955 --> 00:16:06,708
And there, you will
be told what to do.

296
00:16:06,708 --> 00:16:07,709
Now, go.

297
00:16:07,709 --> 00:16:08,710
All right.

298
00:16:08,710 --> 00:16:09,586
Quickly.

299
00:16:09,586 --> 00:16:11,088
Don't waste any more time.

300
00:16:11,088 --> 00:16:11,588
Run.

301
00:16:11,588 --> 00:16:12,089
Run?

302
00:16:12,089 --> 00:16:12,881
But why?

303
00:16:12,881 --> 00:16:16,218
Because the well-intended may
not know what's best at all!

304
00:16:16,218 --> 00:16:16,718
That way!

305
00:16:16,718 --> 00:16:17,469
I think I hear him!

306
00:16:17,469 --> 00:16:18,720
What?

307
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:19,721
Come on.

308
00:16:19,721 --> 00:16:21,723
Run!

309
00:16:21,723 --> 00:16:22,724
Right behind you!

310
00:16:22,724 --> 00:16:26,228
[TENSE MUSIC]

311
00:16:28,189 --> 00:16:28,689
There!

312
00:16:28,689 --> 00:16:32,693
I think I see him now!

313
00:16:32,693 --> 00:16:33,694
Christian!

314
00:16:36,697 --> 00:16:37,698
Christian!

315
00:16:37,698 --> 00:16:39,200
For goodness sake.

316
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,201
[BOTH GRUNTING]

317
00:16:40,201 --> 00:16:41,702
Get over here.

318
00:16:45,706 --> 00:16:47,708
[BOTH PANTING]

319
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:51,212
Obstinate?

320
00:16:51,212 --> 00:16:53,214
What are you doing here?

321
00:16:53,214 --> 00:16:56,092
Trying to keep you from making
a greater fool of yourself

322
00:16:56,092 --> 00:16:57,843
than you already have.

323
00:16:57,843 --> 00:16:59,886
Your wife told me
what happened, and--

324
00:16:59,886 --> 00:17:01,097
I need to get to--

325
00:17:01,097 --> 00:17:02,889
No, I will not let go
until you promise

326
00:17:02,889 --> 00:17:04,725
to listen to reason.

327
00:17:04,725 --> 00:17:05,934
I must.

328
00:17:05,934 --> 00:17:07,186
Nope.

329
00:17:07,186 --> 00:17:07,728
Not budging.

330
00:17:10,564 --> 00:17:11,440
All right.

331
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,692
All right.

332
00:17:13,692 --> 00:17:15,319
Finally.

333
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,612
[LIGHT PLODDING MUSIC]

334
00:17:16,612 --> 00:17:20,074
Well, Pliable, thanks
for being my backup.

335
00:17:20,074 --> 00:17:21,117
You got him.

336
00:17:21,117 --> 00:17:22,076
Well?

337
00:17:22,076 --> 00:17:23,827
Ready to go back?

338
00:17:23,827 --> 00:17:25,329
No.

339
00:17:25,329 --> 00:17:26,497
All right, then.

340
00:17:26,497 --> 00:17:28,082
Have a good trip.

341
00:17:28,082 --> 00:17:30,459
Get back here.

342
00:17:30,459 --> 00:17:31,377
Sure.

343
00:17:31,377 --> 00:17:33,754
And where are you going?

344
00:17:33,754 --> 00:17:35,214
I said I'd listen.

345
00:17:35,214 --> 00:17:36,965
I didn't say I'd stop.

346
00:17:36,965 --> 00:17:40,344
Oh, bother.

347
00:17:40,344 --> 00:17:41,595
Wait for me, Christian.

348
00:17:46,683 --> 00:17:50,229
And why on Earth would
we leave all we love?

349
00:17:50,229 --> 00:17:51,438
Yeah.

350
00:17:51,438 --> 00:17:52,689
Why?

351
00:17:52,689 --> 00:17:55,442
Because it pales by
comparison to all

352
00:17:55,442 --> 00:17:57,068
that the King of
the Celestial City

353
00:17:57,068 --> 00:17:59,321
promises to his subjects--

354
00:17:59,321 --> 00:18:02,574
fullness of joy in the
presence of the King.

355
00:18:02,574 --> 00:18:03,950
Oh.

356
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,369
No more sorrow.

357
00:18:05,369 --> 00:18:06,245
Whoa.

358
00:18:06,245 --> 00:18:08,455
Streets paved with gold.

359
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,332
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha!

360
00:18:10,332 --> 00:18:15,212
The city I leave behind is
filled with evil and misery.

361
00:18:15,212 --> 00:18:16,588
He's got a point there.

362
00:18:16,588 --> 00:18:17,464
Will you be quiet?

363
00:18:17,464 --> 00:18:19,216
You're really not helping.

364
00:18:19,216 --> 00:18:20,717
All right.

365
00:18:20,717 --> 00:18:23,970
The city I seek is
all goodness and joy

366
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:25,472
and lasts forever.

367
00:18:27,849 --> 00:18:30,811
I want to find that city
and come back to tell others

368
00:18:30,811 --> 00:18:32,563
how to get there.

369
00:18:32,563 --> 00:18:35,232
You can read about it all
right here in the Book.

370
00:18:35,232 --> 00:18:36,817
See?

371
00:18:36,817 --> 00:18:38,068
No, I don't see.

372
00:18:38,068 --> 00:18:41,071
And quite frankly,
I don't want to.

373
00:18:41,071 --> 00:18:43,365
That Book, which
you should never

374
00:18:43,365 --> 00:18:45,742
have taken in the first
place, has done nothing

375
00:18:45,742 --> 00:18:49,705
but set you on a
journey to a dream.

376
00:18:49,705 --> 00:18:51,957
Speaking of which,
it's getting late,

377
00:18:51,957 --> 00:18:54,335
and I miss my pillow.

378
00:18:54,335 --> 00:18:59,089
So, will you go with me or
not, you stubborn-headed man?

379
00:18:59,089 --> 00:19:02,343
I was going to ask
you the same thing.

380
00:19:02,343 --> 00:19:04,720
Well, I see you, too,
are obstinate, though

381
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:07,223
for all the wrong reasons.

382
00:19:07,223 --> 00:19:08,224
Come along, Pliable.

383
00:19:08,224 --> 00:19:09,225
Let him go on.

384
00:19:09,225 --> 00:19:10,100
We tried.

385
00:19:14,313 --> 00:19:16,357
Did you not hear me?

386
00:19:16,357 --> 00:19:17,941
Did you not hear him?

387
00:19:17,941 --> 00:19:19,318
Streets of gold.

388
00:19:19,318 --> 00:19:21,320
No more sorrow.

389
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,238
What?

390
00:19:22,238 --> 00:19:24,490
Don't be a fool.

391
00:19:24,490 --> 00:19:25,699
All right.

392
00:19:25,699 --> 00:19:27,368
Well, then?

393
00:19:27,368 --> 00:19:28,702
Endless work.

394
00:19:28,702 --> 00:19:31,121
Things falling apart.

395
00:19:31,121 --> 00:19:32,706
Streets of gold.

396
00:19:32,706 --> 00:19:35,125
No more sorrow.

397
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:37,628
Hmm.

398
00:19:37,628 --> 00:19:39,963
See ya.

399
00:19:39,963 --> 00:19:41,215
Well.

400
00:19:41,215 --> 00:19:44,468
I find no harm in
changing my mind.

401
00:19:44,468 --> 00:19:46,845
Obviously.

402
00:19:46,845 --> 00:19:50,140
Are you sure you won't
change yours, Obstinate?

403
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:52,684
Do I look like I want to?

404
00:19:52,684 --> 00:19:55,687
You fools, walking
to your death.

405
00:19:55,687 --> 00:19:56,855
Oh.

406
00:19:56,855 --> 00:19:59,233
Your poor wife and
the Supervisors

407
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:02,569
shall have my full report.

408
00:20:02,569 --> 00:20:06,573
So streets of gold,
no more sorrow.

409
00:20:06,573 --> 00:20:07,449
Tell on.

410
00:20:07,449 --> 00:20:08,575
What else?

411
00:20:08,575 --> 00:20:10,118
Life unending.

412
00:20:10,118 --> 00:20:11,703
Peace of heart.

413
00:20:11,703 --> 00:20:14,456
Joy forever in the
presence of the King.

414
00:20:14,456 --> 00:20:16,250
Shining garments.

415
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:19,961
Oh, what bliss.

416
00:20:19,961 --> 00:20:23,214
What are we waiting for?

417
00:20:23,214 --> 00:20:25,091
Let's get there as
soon as possible!

418
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:26,843
[BOTH SHOUT]

419
00:20:30,221 --> 00:20:33,224
[HEAVY MUSIC]

420
00:20:33,224 --> 00:20:35,852
What is this?

421
00:20:35,852 --> 00:20:36,353
Oh.

422
00:20:41,483 --> 00:20:42,108
Mud?

423
00:20:45,987 --> 00:20:47,364
Mud?

424
00:20:48,865 --> 00:20:50,576
Pliable?

425
00:20:50,576 --> 00:20:51,327
Are you all--

426
00:20:52,703 --> 00:20:53,620
take my--

427
00:20:54,830 --> 00:20:57,583
I knew I shouldn't
have listened to you.

428
00:21:00,461 --> 00:21:01,337
Here.

429
00:21:01,337 --> 00:21:04,840
Streets of gold.

430
00:21:06,091 --> 00:21:08,594
Shining garments.

431
00:21:14,224 --> 00:21:17,102
Shining garments.

432
00:21:17,102 --> 00:21:20,731
If this is what it's like to
follow you in the beginning,

433
00:21:20,731 --> 00:21:25,569
how could it possibly be
any better in the end?

434
00:21:25,569 --> 00:21:29,698
So much for your Book.

435
00:21:29,698 --> 00:21:33,869
I have no problem
changing my mind.

436
00:21:33,869 --> 00:21:35,329
No, sir.

437
00:21:35,329 --> 00:21:37,748
Please!

438
00:21:37,748 --> 00:21:39,750
Help me!

439
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:43,211
[TENSE MUSIC]

440
00:21:44,713 --> 00:21:46,715
[TWINKLING MUSIC]

441
00:21:54,598 --> 00:21:56,224
You called?

442
00:21:56,224 --> 00:21:58,602
Huh?

443
00:21:58,602 --> 00:22:00,562
I called for help.

444
00:22:00,562 --> 00:22:02,063
I didn't know what else to do.

445
00:22:05,108 --> 00:22:09,237
And I have come,
for that is my name.

446
00:22:09,237 --> 00:22:11,448
Oh.

447
00:22:11,448 --> 00:22:12,073
Thank you.

448
00:22:15,452 --> 00:22:17,996
Better?

449
00:22:17,996 --> 00:22:21,207
Why didn't you use the steps?

450
00:22:21,207 --> 00:22:21,958
Steps?

451
00:22:21,958 --> 00:22:25,379
[GENTLE MUSIC]

452
00:22:26,838 --> 00:22:27,589
Covered again.

453
00:22:32,636 --> 00:22:36,264
The King placed them there
to help people like you.

454
00:22:36,264 --> 00:22:39,435
But no sooner is
the swamp drained

455
00:22:39,435 --> 00:22:43,855
that it fills to overflowing
again with the fears, doubts,

456
00:22:43,855 --> 00:22:48,109
and discouragement of those
that make it this far.

457
00:22:48,109 --> 00:22:50,195
So this is--

458
00:22:50,195 --> 00:22:51,947
Yes.

459
00:22:51,947 --> 00:22:53,574
Looks like mud.

460
00:22:53,574 --> 00:22:55,241
Sticks like mud.

461
00:22:55,241 --> 00:23:03,208
And it'll keep a
person down like mud.

462
00:23:03,208 --> 00:23:04,751
But it isn't.

463
00:23:04,751 --> 00:23:10,591
It's a mess of fears,
the Swamp of Despondency.

464
00:23:13,134 --> 00:23:15,762
The place where people
like your friend

465
00:23:15,762 --> 00:23:19,390
there give up before
they even start.

466
00:23:19,390 --> 00:23:21,560
But it was right, you know.

467
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,436
Right?

468
00:23:22,436 --> 00:23:23,729
To go back, I mean.

469
00:23:23,729 --> 00:23:24,354
But--

470
00:23:24,354 --> 00:23:30,068
This journey you're embarking
on, not for the double-minded.

471
00:23:30,068 --> 00:23:31,236
No, no.

472
00:23:31,236 --> 00:23:33,321
Not for the wishy-washy.

473
00:23:33,321 --> 00:23:34,072
Not at all.

474
00:23:36,992 --> 00:23:41,580
And this swamp, it's
nothing compared

475
00:23:41,580 --> 00:23:43,123
to the trouble that's ahead.

476
00:23:46,334 --> 00:23:49,087
Let me ask you a question.

477
00:23:49,087 --> 00:23:51,965
Do you know
the Celestial King?

478
00:23:51,965 --> 00:23:53,341
He sent me here.

479
00:23:55,719 --> 00:23:58,013
Have you seen the
Celestial City?

480
00:23:58,013 --> 00:23:58,972
I surely have.

481
00:23:58,972 --> 00:24:00,766
Then step aside.

482
00:24:00,766 --> 00:24:03,059
I know the way will be rough.

483
00:24:03,059 --> 00:24:06,062
I've read about
that in the Book.

484
00:24:06,062 --> 00:24:08,189
I can only hope
for the King's help

485
00:24:08,189 --> 00:24:11,234
as I continue on
my journey, which

486
00:24:11,234 --> 00:24:14,696
I am determined to complete.

487
00:24:14,696 --> 00:24:18,449
And I need no
convincing, Christian,

488
00:24:18,449 --> 00:24:20,368
for I have no
doubts that you have

489
00:24:20,368 --> 00:24:24,498
turned your face to the light
and are not looking back.

490
00:24:24,498 --> 00:24:26,082
Continue your trek.

491
00:24:28,710 --> 00:24:30,962
And do not forget.

492
00:24:30,962 --> 00:24:37,010
Help, in some form or
another, is never far away.

493
00:24:37,010 --> 00:24:38,887
Thank you, again, for--

494
00:24:38,887 --> 00:24:39,721
[GRUNTS]

495
00:24:41,472 --> 00:24:43,266
It's mud.

496
00:24:43,266 --> 00:24:45,686
You still had a little
bit of mud on you.

497
00:24:45,686 --> 00:24:46,562
[CLEARS THROAT]

498
00:24:47,062 --> 00:24:48,939
Farewell!

499
00:24:48,939 --> 00:24:55,195
Remember-- help, in some form
or another, is never far away.

500
00:24:59,616 --> 00:25:03,078
[HEAVY MUSIC]

501
00:25:06,957 --> 00:25:07,624
Oh, dear.

502
00:25:07,624 --> 00:25:07,958
Oh, dear.

503
00:25:07,958 --> 00:25:08,458
Oh, dear.

504
00:25:08,458 --> 00:25:08,959
Oh, dear.

505
00:25:08,959 --> 00:25:09,459
Oh, dear.

506
00:25:12,378 --> 00:25:15,632
Another man has gone...

507
00:25:15,632 --> 00:25:16,257
Oh.

508
00:25:16,257 --> 00:25:17,133
You've heard already.

509
00:25:21,137 --> 00:25:24,600
Yes, I did.

510
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:28,311
And so has the
Master, obviously.

511
00:25:28,311 --> 00:25:31,732
He has gone beyond the
swamp into the outer realms.

512
00:25:31,732 --> 00:25:35,944
So there's nothing we can do.

513
00:25:35,944 --> 00:25:37,445
Oh, but there is.

514
00:25:37,445 --> 00:25:40,574
In the outer realms,
we cannot impede him.

515
00:25:40,574 --> 00:25:45,453
But we can dissuade him with
fear, with doubt, with pride.

516
00:25:45,453 --> 00:25:48,456
There are many,
many persuasions.

517
00:25:48,456 --> 00:25:50,458
[LAUGHS]

518
00:25:53,503 --> 00:25:55,964
[BOTH LAUGHING]

519
00:26:06,767 --> 00:26:10,228
[SOFT MUSIC]

520
00:26:13,189 --> 00:26:16,818
What I wouldn't do to
get rid of this thing.

521
00:26:21,197 --> 00:26:24,325
I'd give anything
in the world to--

522
00:26:24,325 --> 00:26:27,829
[LIGHT TWINKLING MUSIC]

523
00:26:45,221 --> 00:26:47,473
Whatever is the
matter, dear boy?

524
00:26:47,473 --> 00:26:51,853
And what in the world is that
awful thing on your back?

525
00:26:51,853 --> 00:26:54,940
I'm actually on my way to--

526
00:26:54,940 --> 00:26:56,692
Where are my manners?

527
00:26:56,692 --> 00:26:58,193
Worldly's the name.

528
00:26:58,193 --> 00:27:01,112
Worldly first, Wiseman
last, of course.

529
00:27:01,112 --> 00:27:03,614
Don't ever mix them up.

530
00:27:03,614 --> 00:27:06,702
You were saying?

531
00:27:06,702 --> 00:27:10,205
That I am on my way
to the Celestial City

532
00:27:10,205 --> 00:27:11,707
by way of the gate,

533
00:27:11,707 --> 00:27:14,960
where I hope to get
rid of this burden which is

534
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:17,628
getting bigger by the hour.

535
00:27:17,628 --> 00:27:21,466
Oh, and you would do well
to do that, dear boy.

536
00:27:21,466 --> 00:27:23,468
But--

537
00:27:23,468 --> 00:27:24,135
Yes?

538
00:27:24,135 --> 00:27:28,348
Well, who told you you could
get rid of that over there?

539
00:27:28,348 --> 00:27:32,477
A good man that came upon me
in my hour of need, Evang--

540
00:27:32,477 --> 00:27:35,313
--gelist, of course.

541
00:27:35,313 --> 00:27:36,314
Oh, dear, dear, dear.

542
00:27:36,314 --> 00:27:37,315
[TSKS]

543
00:27:37,315 --> 00:27:38,108
What is it?

544
00:27:38,108 --> 00:27:40,193
And you've already
come all this way.

545
00:27:40,193 --> 00:27:41,111
Oh, dear, dear, dear.

546
00:27:41,111 --> 00:27:42,946
Well, what?

547
00:27:42,946 --> 00:27:45,323
It's just that
this Evangelist--

548
00:27:47,951 --> 00:27:49,494
Yes?

549
00:27:49,494 --> 00:27:52,080
Well, he's a little--

550
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,999
[COOING]

551
00:27:56,459 --> 00:27:58,086
So he's--

552
00:27:58,086 --> 00:27:59,713
Yes, he is.

553
00:27:59,713 --> 00:28:01,214
Loony as a bird.

554
00:28:01,214 --> 00:28:03,008
The poor chap has his
head in the clouds.

555
00:28:03,008 --> 00:28:04,885
Oh, no.

556
00:28:04,885 --> 00:28:07,888
So what on Earth was
this Evangelist thinking,

557
00:28:07,888 --> 00:28:10,223
sending you in that direction?

558
00:28:10,223 --> 00:28:12,683
Full of nothing but
trouble and danger,

559
00:28:12,683 --> 00:28:14,060
which I can see
by the scratches

560
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:15,603
and the tears and the mud,

561
00:28:15,603 --> 00:28:18,481
you've already experienced.

562
00:28:18,481 --> 00:28:22,193
So don't go that direction,
which is silly nonsense.

563
00:28:22,193 --> 00:28:25,947
But you go in this
direction, which is not.

564
00:28:25,947 --> 00:28:26,865
But--

565
00:28:26,865 --> 00:28:27,949
No "but."

566
00:28:27,949 --> 00:28:29,242
Do not argue with me.

567
00:28:29,242 --> 00:28:30,326
You listen.

568
00:28:30,326 --> 00:28:33,246
So you keep going that way.

569
00:28:33,246 --> 00:28:36,457
[LIGHT PLODDING MUSIC]

570
00:28:37,834 --> 00:28:38,835
Good boy.

571
00:28:38,835 --> 00:28:42,213
You keep going that
way, and do not stop.

572
00:28:42,213 --> 00:28:45,341
No matter what things
begin to look like, just

573
00:28:45,341 --> 00:28:50,721
go in the direction I
tell you until you get

574
00:28:50,721 --> 00:28:53,724
to a village called Morality.

575
00:28:56,436 --> 00:29:00,231
There, you will find the Hill.

576
00:29:00,231 --> 00:29:02,859
You will know you're at the
Hill because the signs will

577
00:29:02,859 --> 00:29:04,444
tell you.

578
00:29:04,444 --> 00:29:08,073
There, not at that silly gate
you were telling me about,

579
00:29:08,073 --> 00:29:11,827
you will be told how to
get rid of that ugly thing.

580
00:29:11,827 --> 00:29:15,746
[HEAVY MUSIC]

581
00:29:15,746 --> 00:29:17,248
Who goes there?

582
00:29:20,210 --> 00:29:26,883
I say, who goes there?

583
00:29:26,883 --> 00:29:29,719
My name is Christian.

584
00:29:29,719 --> 00:29:32,722
I was told to ask
for a gentleman

585
00:29:32,722 --> 00:29:37,936
by the name of Legality.

586
00:29:37,936 --> 00:29:41,815
A man, I am, of sorts.

587
00:29:41,815 --> 00:29:45,193
But gentle, I am not.

588
00:29:45,193 --> 00:29:47,195
[LAUGHS]

589
00:29:50,615 --> 00:29:55,370
I was told that you
could get rid of this--

590
00:29:55,370 --> 00:29:58,957
Stop your blubbering,
and get on with it.

591
00:29:58,957 --> 00:30:02,585
I've haven't got all day.

592
00:30:02,585 --> 00:30:07,382
That you could get rid
of this burden for me.

593
00:30:07,382 --> 00:30:09,717
Indeed, I can.

594
00:30:09,717 --> 00:30:10,635
Oh.

595
00:30:10,635 --> 00:30:12,971
Well, then, please.

596
00:30:12,971 --> 00:30:13,972
Will you?

597
00:30:13,972 --> 00:30:18,309
Well, I can't very well
come down to you now, can I?

598
00:30:18,309 --> 00:30:21,187
I am a mountain!

599
00:30:21,187 --> 00:30:23,564
You will have to come to me.

600
00:30:23,564 --> 00:30:25,483
But how?

601
00:30:25,483 --> 00:30:28,319
Follow the instructions.

602
00:30:28,319 --> 00:30:30,571
Which ones?

603
00:30:30,571 --> 00:30:33,074
All of them, of course.

604
00:30:33,074 --> 00:30:34,325
Which ones?

605
00:30:34,325 --> 00:30:35,076
[LAUGHS]

606
00:30:35,076 --> 00:30:37,578
But there are too many.

607
00:30:37,578 --> 00:30:38,955
Too many?

608
00:30:38,955 --> 00:30:40,456
Too many?

609
00:30:40,456 --> 00:30:42,833
Why, can there ever be enough?

610
00:30:42,833 --> 00:30:44,210
[CHRISTIAN WHIMPERS]

611
00:30:44,210 --> 00:30:45,879
Come now.

612
00:30:45,879 --> 00:30:48,464
You want that burden
off, don't you?

613
00:30:48,464 --> 00:30:49,883
Come to me.

614
00:30:49,883 --> 00:30:51,092
But--

615
00:30:51,092 --> 00:30:52,718
Do as I say.

616
00:30:52,718 --> 00:30:55,096
Come, now.

617
00:30:55,096 --> 00:30:56,973
You're still too far away.

618
00:30:56,973 --> 00:31:00,101
I can hardly see you now.

619
00:31:00,101 --> 00:31:00,936
Keep up, man.

620
00:31:00,936 --> 00:31:01,686
Keep up.

621
00:31:01,686 --> 00:31:04,689
I can't do the work for you.

622
00:31:04,689 --> 00:31:06,066
You missed a sign there.

623
00:31:06,066 --> 00:31:07,192
You missed one, I say.

624
00:31:10,361 --> 00:31:12,822
I can't.

625
00:31:12,822 --> 00:31:14,199
[CHRISTIAN SCREAMS]

626
00:31:16,617 --> 00:31:20,705
You expect me to help you when
you cannot even help yourself?

627
00:31:20,705 --> 00:31:21,872
On your feet.

628
00:31:21,872 --> 00:31:23,083
Oh.

629
00:31:23,083 --> 00:31:24,875
What am I going to do?

630
00:31:24,875 --> 00:31:26,377
[FOOTSTEPS]

631
00:31:26,377 --> 00:31:27,337
[GASP]

632
00:31:27,337 --> 00:31:30,256
Uh-oh.

633
00:31:30,256 --> 00:31:34,469
How is it you've turned
out of the way so quickly?

634
00:31:34,469 --> 00:31:35,720
I don't know.

635
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:36,221
Ha!

636
00:31:36,972 --> 00:31:38,889
Oh, dear.

637
00:31:38,889 --> 00:31:41,684
Ow!

638
00:31:41,684 --> 00:31:42,685
Come on.

639
00:31:42,685 --> 00:31:45,063
Let's get you out
from under all that.

640
00:31:45,063 --> 00:31:48,066
Commandments cannot give
you what you seek, Christian.

641
00:31:48,066 --> 00:31:50,443
They will only be a
reminder that you are not

642
00:31:50,443 --> 00:31:51,861
able to keep them all.

643
00:31:51,861 --> 00:31:55,198
Legality can never rid you
of your burden, you know.

644
00:31:55,198 --> 00:31:57,117
Say what?

645
00:31:57,117 --> 00:31:58,243
I said--

646
00:31:58,243 --> 00:32:00,578
I'll show you what I can do.

647
00:32:00,578 --> 00:32:04,582
Prepare to see my
power, you wretched man.

648
00:32:04,582 --> 00:32:05,458
Christian!

649
00:32:05,458 --> 00:32:06,876
Run!

650
00:32:06,876 --> 00:32:09,212
Bury you are under the
weight of my power,

651
00:32:09,212 --> 00:32:15,343
I will, and rid the world
of your burden and you.

652
00:32:15,343 --> 00:32:18,346
[LEGALITY GRUNTS]

653
00:32:18,346 --> 00:32:19,847
[CHRISTIAN SHOUTS]

654
00:32:21,349 --> 00:32:23,309
[LEGALITY LAUGHS]

655
00:32:23,309 --> 00:32:26,729
[TENSE HEAVY MUSIC]

656
00:32:36,739 --> 00:32:38,741
[COUGHING]

657
00:32:42,328 --> 00:32:44,998
Here we are.

658
00:32:44,998 --> 00:32:47,333
When Legality comes
toppling down,

659
00:32:47,333 --> 00:32:50,628
we are catapulted
to the way, the way

660
00:32:50,628 --> 00:32:53,964
that you left off following.

661
00:32:56,592 --> 00:33:00,096
It wasn't really my fault.

662
00:33:00,096 --> 00:33:03,224
Oh, I see.

663
00:33:03,224 --> 00:33:06,561
A man I met, a Mr. Worldly--

664
00:33:06,561 --> 00:33:07,978
Ah.

665
00:33:07,978 --> 00:33:10,565
That scoundrel.

666
00:33:10,565 --> 00:33:13,193
Well, he said there
was an easier way

667
00:33:13,193 --> 00:33:14,569
to get rid of my burden.

668
00:33:14,569 --> 00:33:16,446
And I-- well, I--

669
00:33:16,446 --> 00:33:19,865
Was led out of this way.

670
00:33:19,865 --> 00:33:20,366
I thought--

671
00:33:20,366 --> 00:33:23,994
You thought the King was
leading you down a wrong path.

672
00:33:23,994 --> 00:33:24,995
Well, no.

673
00:33:24,995 --> 00:33:26,081
I--

674
00:33:26,081 --> 00:33:28,958
You brought this
misery upon yourself

675
00:33:28,958 --> 00:33:31,711
by rejecting the very
instructions the King sent

676
00:33:31,711 --> 00:33:33,129
to you, Christian.

677
00:33:33,129 --> 00:33:35,590
You're right.

678
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:39,135
It is my fault.
I had no business

679
00:33:39,135 --> 00:33:41,721
listening to Worldly Wiseman.

680
00:33:41,721 --> 00:33:43,848
It's no one's fault but mine.

681
00:33:43,848 --> 00:33:45,475
And I'm sorry.

682
00:33:45,475 --> 00:33:45,975
I'm--

683
00:33:45,975 --> 00:33:47,685
Forgiven.

684
00:33:47,685 --> 00:33:48,853
What?

685
00:33:48,853 --> 00:33:49,729
I'm--

686
00:33:49,729 --> 00:33:51,939
Forgiven.

687
00:33:51,939 --> 00:33:56,611
If tears are any indication
of regret, yours are.

688
00:33:56,611 --> 00:34:01,699
The King has said every
misstep will be forgiven.

689
00:34:01,699 --> 00:34:04,369
Now, stand up.

690
00:34:04,369 --> 00:34:07,830
Continue the journey, for
you have no time to lose.

691
00:34:07,830 --> 00:34:10,708
But learn, Christian,
that there are two things

692
00:34:10,708 --> 00:34:12,960
this deceiver
caused you to do.

693
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:17,215
The first is that he caused
you to so easily go out

694
00:34:17,215 --> 00:34:20,218
of the way and,
second, that he made

695
00:34:20,218 --> 00:34:25,598
the difficulty of your journey
something you wanted to avoid.

696
00:34:25,598 --> 00:34:28,184
Now, off to the gate with you.

697
00:34:28,184 --> 00:34:32,605
And remember, good Christian,
do not leave the path again.

698
00:34:32,605 --> 00:34:36,066
[LIGHT MUSIC]

699
00:34:37,067 --> 00:34:40,446
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

700
00:34:41,947 --> 00:34:46,244
You failed miserably.

701
00:34:46,244 --> 00:34:49,372
But I got him to
go out of the way.

702
00:34:49,372 --> 00:34:53,209
And then you left him.

703
00:34:53,209 --> 00:34:55,461
In the hands of Worldly
Wiseman and Legality.

704
00:34:55,461 --> 00:34:58,214
I was certain he would
be caught in their maze.

705
00:34:58,214 --> 00:34:58,881
He was ours.

706
00:34:58,881 --> 00:35:01,134
He was ours.

707
00:35:01,134 --> 00:35:04,220
And now he is not.

708
00:35:04,220 --> 00:35:06,639
[RUMBLING]

709
00:35:09,642 --> 00:35:10,560
[SHOUT]

710
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,061
[GROWLING]

711
00:35:14,564 --> 00:35:16,566
What would you have me do?

712
00:35:16,566 --> 00:35:19,194
Get the others.

713
00:35:19,194 --> 00:35:21,696
Send out the legion.

714
00:35:21,696 --> 00:35:25,074
Do what you must.

715
00:35:25,074 --> 00:35:26,075
Yes, Master.

716
00:35:26,075 --> 00:35:26,576
Yes.

717
00:35:30,079 --> 00:35:33,082
Do not let him near that gate.

718
00:35:33,082 --> 00:35:35,084
Stop him.

719
00:35:35,084 --> 00:35:36,085
Stop him!

720
00:35:36,085 --> 00:35:39,505
[INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

721
00:35:43,509 --> 00:35:47,472
[SOFT FOREBODING MUSIC]

722
00:36:10,828 --> 00:36:12,830
[RUSTLING]

723
00:36:13,831 --> 00:36:15,333
[SOFT GROWL]

724
00:36:26,219 --> 00:36:28,221
[PANTING]

725
00:36:30,223 --> 00:36:31,724
Oh.

726
00:36:31,724 --> 00:36:32,725
Calm down.

727
00:36:47,573 --> 00:36:49,575
[INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

728
00:36:49,575 --> 00:36:51,076
[SCREAM]

729
00:36:52,578 --> 00:36:53,996
[GROWL]

730
00:36:56,999 --> 00:36:59,502
[CREATURES GROWLING]

731
00:37:15,435 --> 00:37:17,437
[SCREAM]

732
00:37:31,367 --> 00:37:32,993
The gate.

733
00:37:32,993 --> 00:37:34,954
[LAUGHS] At last.

734
00:37:34,954 --> 00:37:38,458
[LIGHT MUSIC]

735
00:37:41,961 --> 00:37:45,381
[HEAVY DRAMATIC MUSIC]

736
00:37:45,381 --> 00:37:47,883
[CREATURES SCREECHING]

737
00:38:08,195 --> 00:38:10,197
Help will come in
some form or another.

738
00:38:10,197 --> 00:38:11,699
Help will-- help!

739
00:38:11,699 --> 00:38:12,700
Help!

740
00:38:12,700 --> 00:38:16,120
[ETHEREAL MUSIC]

741
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:17,622
Knock, and it will be--

742
00:38:17,622 --> 00:38:19,123
[CREATURES GROWLING]

743
00:38:24,629 --> 00:38:26,213
Open the door!

744
00:38:26,213 --> 00:38:27,715
Yes?

745
00:38:27,715 --> 00:38:29,008
My name is Christian, and I--

746
00:38:29,008 --> 00:38:29,509
Yes?

747
00:38:29,509 --> 00:38:30,885
Let me in!

748
00:38:30,885 --> 00:38:31,719
Ah.

749
00:38:31,719 --> 00:38:32,512
The very words.

750
00:38:41,937 --> 00:38:43,188
I made it.

751
00:38:45,566 --> 00:38:47,067
I made it.

752
00:38:47,067 --> 00:38:51,113
For a moment, I thought
I wouldn't, but I did.

753
00:38:51,113 --> 00:38:52,948
Ha! I did.

754
00:38:52,948 --> 00:38:55,200
No one gets turned away here.

755
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:58,579
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

756
00:39:08,756 --> 00:39:10,090
What are you doing?

757
00:39:10,090 --> 00:39:13,386
Well, I was told this would
come off once I got here.

758
00:39:13,386 --> 00:39:15,888
I believe the words
were, "And there, you

759
00:39:15,888 --> 00:39:17,598
will be told what to do."

760
00:39:17,598 --> 00:39:18,348
Oh.

761
00:39:18,348 --> 00:39:20,100
Very well, then.

762
00:39:20,100 --> 00:39:24,439
I'd say you'd better run.

763
00:39:24,439 --> 00:39:25,690
Run?

764
00:39:25,690 --> 00:39:27,692
And by the looks of it,
the sooner, the better.

765
00:39:27,692 --> 00:39:30,445
Come on.

766
00:39:30,445 --> 00:39:32,447
But I thought my
journey was over.

767
00:39:32,447 --> 00:39:33,322
Over?

768
00:39:33,322 --> 00:39:34,449
Oh, no, dear boy.

769
00:39:34,449 --> 00:39:35,700
Your journey's just beginning.

770
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,618
And if I were you, I'd--

771
00:39:37,618 --> 00:39:39,328
[GROWLING]

772
00:39:39,328 --> 00:39:41,205
--make a dash for it now.

773
00:39:41,205 --> 00:39:41,706
But--

774
00:39:41,706 --> 00:39:43,207
Go, quickly!

775
00:39:43,207 --> 00:39:45,334
But how will I know
which way to go?

776
00:39:45,334 --> 00:39:46,251
The straight path.

777
00:39:46,251 --> 00:39:47,336
Always the straight.

778
00:39:47,336 --> 00:39:51,381
It will lead you
to the Interpreter.

779
00:39:51,381 --> 00:39:52,382
Now, go.

780
00:39:52,382 --> 00:39:55,720
[INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

781
00:39:56,721 --> 00:39:59,139
[MAN SHOUTS]

782
00:39:59,139 --> 00:40:03,060
Come and get it,
you winged rats!

783
00:40:03,060 --> 00:40:04,437
Slime bags!

784
00:40:04,437 --> 00:40:05,438
Take that!

785
00:40:09,358 --> 00:40:11,861
[CREATURES SCREECHING]

786
00:40:11,861 --> 00:40:13,863
[MAN GRUNTING]

787
00:40:13,863 --> 00:40:17,324
[POWERFUL DRAMATIC MUSIC]

788
00:40:32,214 --> 00:40:35,635
[SOFT MUSIC]

789
00:40:43,851 --> 00:40:44,351
Ow!

790
00:40:49,607 --> 00:40:52,693
I could sure use
some help about now.

791
00:40:52,693 --> 00:40:56,196
[TWINKLING MUSIC]

792
00:41:00,075 --> 00:41:01,076
[LAUGH]

793
00:41:05,956 --> 00:41:09,001
What is this?

794
00:41:09,001 --> 00:41:10,961
[LAUGH]

795
00:41:42,201 --> 00:41:45,329
You want me to follow you?

796
00:41:45,329 --> 00:41:47,247
[LAUGH]

797
00:41:54,213 --> 00:41:56,716
[CHRISTIAN LAUGHING]

798
00:42:09,061 --> 00:42:10,062
[GRUNT]

799
00:42:11,564 --> 00:42:14,984
[LIGHT GENTLE MUSIC]

800
00:42:16,485 --> 00:42:17,945
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

801
00:42:26,453 --> 00:42:27,955
Who are you?

802
00:42:27,955 --> 00:42:30,332
My dear, dear boy.

803
00:42:30,332 --> 00:42:33,878
Why, I am the Interpreter.

804
00:42:37,339 --> 00:42:39,466
I've been expecting you.

805
00:42:39,466 --> 00:42:43,846
And I was expecting
a house of some sort.

806
00:42:43,846 --> 00:42:47,474
Things are not always what
they seem, dear Christian.

807
00:42:47,474 --> 00:42:50,560
And sometimes, life's
tumbles can lead you

808
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:54,106
to the most
interesting of places.

809
00:42:54,106 --> 00:42:58,110
The Gatekeeper was right to
say you would be helped here.

810
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:03,240
Is there something the matter?

811
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:06,576
The light, it seems
to follow you.

812
00:43:06,576 --> 00:43:09,371
[LAUGHS] As it should.

813
00:43:09,371 --> 00:43:11,832
I am the Interpreter.

814
00:43:11,832 --> 00:43:15,878
I bring light where
there are shadows.

815
00:43:15,878 --> 00:43:17,212
I see.

816
00:43:17,212 --> 00:43:19,464
Do you really, Christian?

817
00:43:19,464 --> 00:43:20,966
Do I really--

818
00:43:20,966 --> 00:43:25,220
See and understand?

819
00:43:25,220 --> 00:43:29,391
Well, now I'm
beginning not to.

820
00:43:29,391 --> 00:43:33,562
On your way here, you
walked in darkness.

821
00:43:33,562 --> 00:43:38,067
I am here, Christian,
to give light

822
00:43:38,067 --> 00:43:39,985
to the rest of your journey.

823
00:43:39,985 --> 00:43:43,322
[ETHEREAL MUSIC]

824
00:43:47,201 --> 00:43:49,578
Who are they?

825
00:43:49,578 --> 00:43:52,957
We are the followers
of the King who

826
00:43:52,957 --> 00:43:57,586
leads us by way of
the light in His book.

827
00:43:57,586 --> 00:44:00,339
The King's promises
are ever at their side,

828
00:44:00,339 --> 00:44:04,719
and their gaze is to the
things which last forever.

829
00:44:04,719 --> 00:44:07,346
Keep this in mind,
Christian, for you

830
00:44:07,346 --> 00:44:09,598
will meet people
who will pretend

831
00:44:09,598 --> 00:44:14,478
to lead you in the right and
will only lead you into--

832
00:44:14,478 --> 00:44:16,355
[BABY CRYING]

833
00:44:16,355 --> 00:44:18,691
--misery.

834
00:44:18,691 --> 00:44:21,068
And this?

835
00:44:21,068 --> 00:44:22,069
This is--

836
00:44:22,069 --> 00:44:25,614
Passion, who throws a
horrid tantrum because he

837
00:44:25,614 --> 00:44:27,324
wants things.

838
00:44:27,324 --> 00:44:27,825
No!

839
00:44:27,825 --> 00:44:28,325
No!

840
00:44:28,325 --> 00:44:30,577
No!

841
00:44:30,577 --> 00:44:32,121
[INTERPRETER TSKS]

842
00:44:32,121 --> 00:44:34,581
Won't you be a dear
when you grow up?

843
00:44:39,086 --> 00:44:40,880
Patience, on the other hand,

844
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:43,090
[LAUGH]

845
00:44:43,966 --> 00:44:47,720
is happy to enjoy
things as they come.

846
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:52,224
You are learning to look
and not just see, Christian.

847
00:44:52,224 --> 00:44:54,434
Very good.

848
00:44:54,434 --> 00:44:59,189
And the interpretation
here is that...

849
00:44:59,189 --> 00:45:03,110
I must be content to wait
in patience for the things

850
00:45:03,110 --> 00:45:07,990
the King has promised me and
not be tempted out of the way.

851
00:45:07,990 --> 00:45:11,701
The things you have seen will
help you on your journey.

852
00:45:11,701 --> 00:45:14,830
And, lastly--

853
00:45:14,830 --> 00:45:15,330
No!

854
00:45:18,250 --> 00:45:21,711
[SOMBER MUSIC]

855
00:45:26,591 --> 00:45:31,596
If you are wondering why he
remains in the cage, ask him.

856
00:45:34,349 --> 00:45:40,189
Sir, why are you
in such despair?

857
00:45:40,189 --> 00:45:43,692
No hope.

858
00:45:43,692 --> 00:45:46,070
I beg your pardon?

859
00:45:46,070 --> 00:45:47,947
Sir, I cannot hear you.

860
00:45:47,947 --> 00:45:49,448
No hope.

861
00:45:49,448 --> 00:45:50,699
No hope.

862
00:45:50,699 --> 00:45:51,700
No hope!

863
00:45:51,700 --> 00:45:54,203
No hope!

864
00:45:54,203 --> 00:45:58,707
No hope!

865
00:45:58,707 --> 00:45:59,708
No hope!

866
00:45:59,708 --> 00:46:01,710
No hope!

867
00:46:01,710 --> 00:46:03,712
No hope.

868
00:46:13,638 --> 00:46:18,310
That last one, it was
very unpleasant.

869
00:46:18,310 --> 00:46:21,063
As despair can tend to be.

870
00:46:21,063 --> 00:46:23,190
But what did it mean?

871
00:46:23,190 --> 00:46:27,945
That is for you to interpret
when the time comes.

872
00:46:27,945 --> 00:46:31,448
My gift to help
you on your way may

873
00:46:31,448 --> 00:46:35,452
be summed up in these words.

874
00:46:35,452 --> 00:46:36,954
Look.

875
00:46:36,954 --> 00:46:39,373
Do not just see.

876
00:46:39,373 --> 00:46:41,208
Listen.

877
00:46:41,208 --> 00:46:42,626
And--

878
00:46:42,626 --> 00:46:47,131
And do not just hear.

879
00:46:47,131 --> 00:46:51,718
You are ready to
continue your journey.

880
00:46:51,718 --> 00:46:54,471
Ponder the things you
have learned today,

881
00:46:54,471 --> 00:46:57,516
that they may prod
your sides and lead you

882
00:46:57,516 --> 00:47:02,229
to that place your
heart so longs for.

883
00:47:02,229 --> 00:47:05,690
[MUSIC - "BE THOU MY VISION"]

884
00:47:05,690 --> 00:47:14,366
(SINGING) Be Thou my
vision, O Lord of my heart.

885
00:47:14,366 --> 00:47:22,207
Naught be all else to
me, save that Thou art.

886
00:47:22,207 --> 00:47:30,590
Thou my best thought
by day or by night.

887
00:47:30,590 --> 00:47:38,598
Waking or sleeping,
Thy presence my light.

888
00:47:40,350 --> 00:47:42,227
Patience Path.

889
00:47:46,190 --> 00:47:49,609
Passion Passage.

890
00:47:49,609 --> 00:47:52,071
Which one?

891
00:47:52,071 --> 00:47:52,988
Look.

892
00:47:52,988 --> 00:47:53,822
Do not just--

893
00:47:53,822 --> 00:47:54,823
See.

894
00:47:57,242 --> 00:47:59,328
[SIGH] This doesn't
make sense to me.

895
00:48:02,206 --> 00:48:04,708
But I have not gone
wrong to follow

896
00:48:04,708 --> 00:48:08,712
the King's Road, no matter
how difficult it may seem.

897
00:48:08,712 --> 00:48:16,636
(SINGING) Riches I heed
not, nor man's empty praise.

898
00:48:16,636 --> 00:48:23,936
Thou mine inheritance
now and always.

899
00:48:23,936 --> 00:48:31,986
Thou and Thou only,
first in my heart.

900
00:48:31,986 --> 00:48:39,826
High King of heaven,
my treasure Thou art.

901
00:48:45,707 --> 00:48:52,589
If I am to go forward, the
King shall give me strength.

902
00:49:00,472 --> 00:49:05,060
And if He wills
to ease my load--

903
00:49:05,060 --> 00:49:08,480
[LIGHT POWERFUL MUSIC]

904
00:49:10,940 --> 00:49:12,442
What?

905
00:49:12,442 --> 00:49:14,361
[WHOOSHING]

906
00:49:25,705 --> 00:49:27,707
Oh.

907
00:49:27,707 --> 00:49:29,459
Joy!

908
00:49:29,459 --> 00:49:30,877
What am I nearing

909
00:49:30,877 --> 00:49:33,713
that my burden is
finally being loosed?

910
00:49:33,713 --> 00:49:34,714
[LAUGHS]

911
00:49:37,592 --> 00:49:41,596
Oh, I was right to
follow the King's path,

912
00:49:41,596 --> 00:49:50,355
for with each step,
He is setting me free!

913
00:49:50,355 --> 00:49:58,322
(SINGING) High King of
heaven, my victory won.

914
00:49:58,322 --> 00:50:06,205
May I reach heaven's joys,
O bright heaven's sun.

915
00:50:06,205 --> 00:50:13,712
Heart of my own heart,
whatever befall,

916
00:50:13,712 --> 00:50:20,135
still be my vision,
O Ruler of all.

917
00:50:20,135 --> 00:50:21,136
I'm free!

918
00:50:21,136 --> 00:50:25,099
I'm free!

919
00:50:25,099 --> 00:50:27,101
[GLASS SHATTERING]

920
00:50:35,067 --> 00:50:39,363
Do you understand what
just happened, Christian?

921
00:50:39,363 --> 00:50:41,323
Who are you?

922
00:50:41,323 --> 00:50:44,576
We are the King's heralds.

923
00:50:44,576 --> 00:50:48,080
Do you understand
what just happened?

924
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:51,958
My heart, it has
been cleansed.

925
00:50:51,958 --> 00:50:56,838
My King did for me what I
and no one else could do.

926
00:50:56,838 --> 00:50:59,716
He has rid me of my burden.

927
00:50:59,716 --> 00:51:03,595
And He has given me new life.

928
00:51:03,595 --> 00:51:06,390
Indeed, He has.

929
00:51:06,390 --> 00:51:10,810
New garments for a new life.

930
00:51:10,810 --> 00:51:14,939
The King has made
you one of His own.

931
00:51:14,939 --> 00:51:18,818
You walk as a prince
before Him, Christian.

932
00:51:21,946 --> 00:51:27,702
My heart is overwhelmed with
thanks, for my filthy rags

933
00:51:27,702 --> 00:51:31,123
and the heavy burden
have been taken from me.

934
00:51:31,123 --> 00:51:37,379
And in their place, such
blessing, such great blessing

935
00:51:37,379 --> 00:51:40,507
beyond compare.

936
00:51:40,507 --> 00:51:43,593
For now, continue
on your journey

937
00:51:43,593 --> 00:51:46,721
until you reach the
Palace Beautiful.

938
00:51:46,721 --> 00:51:48,640
There, you will be refreshed

939
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:50,975
and readied for
what lies ahead.

940
00:51:54,854 --> 00:51:56,315
[MASTER GROWLS]

941
00:51:56,315 --> 00:51:57,232
[SUPERVISOR GROANS]

942
00:51:57,232 --> 00:52:00,610
[HEAVY OMINOUS MUSIC]

943
00:52:02,070 --> 00:52:03,988
There was nothing we could do.

944
00:52:03,988 --> 00:52:05,574
We tried.

945
00:52:05,574 --> 00:52:08,202
But not well enough.

946
00:52:10,329 --> 00:52:12,622
We--we have failed you.

947
00:52:12,622 --> 00:52:14,583
[MASTER GROWLS]

948
00:52:18,212 --> 00:52:23,132
Perhaps--perhaps he
will simply be forgotten.

949
00:52:23,132 --> 00:52:26,595
Perhaps we should
just let him be.

950
00:52:26,595 --> 00:52:28,096
Let him be?

951
00:52:28,096 --> 00:52:30,349
Let him be?!

952
00:52:30,349 --> 00:52:34,978
The fool is a greater threat
to us now than he was before.

953
00:52:34,978 --> 00:52:36,938
Threat?

954
00:52:36,938 --> 00:52:38,607
But how?

955
00:52:38,607 --> 00:52:40,984
He will not be forgotten.

956
00:52:40,984 --> 00:52:43,945
Others will try
the same thing.

957
00:52:43,945 --> 00:52:44,988
No.

958
00:52:44,988 --> 00:52:47,949
He must be stopped.

959
00:52:47,949 --> 00:52:53,205
But, sire, he bears the seal.

960
00:52:53,205 --> 00:52:56,208
Do you think me that helpless?

961
00:52:56,208 --> 00:52:58,377
Have you not seen
how many I have

962
00:52:58,377 --> 00:53:03,715
caused to turn away even
this far into their journey?

963
00:53:03,715 --> 00:53:09,388
By the time I am through
with this-- this Christian,

964
00:53:09,388 --> 00:53:13,767
he shall be lying in a
pool of his own blood.

965
00:53:19,063 --> 00:53:22,442
[FOREBODING MUSIC]

966
00:53:22,442 --> 00:53:23,943
At last.

967
00:53:26,070 --> 00:53:28,615
[GROWLING]

968
00:53:28,615 --> 00:53:29,449
What was that?

969
00:53:32,076 --> 00:53:34,954
[GROWLING]

970
00:53:34,954 --> 00:53:36,498
What-- what is that?

971
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:43,338
Just forest animals.

972
00:53:43,338 --> 00:53:46,841
[INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

973
00:53:48,843 --> 00:53:50,762
[GROWLING]

974
00:53:56,225 --> 00:53:57,686
What should I do?

975
00:53:57,686 --> 00:53:58,687
What should I do?

976
00:54:02,691 --> 00:54:07,111
I must go forward.

977
00:54:07,111 --> 00:54:09,113
Help.

978
00:54:09,113 --> 00:54:10,490
Help...

979
00:54:14,077 --> 00:54:15,078
Come.

980
00:54:15,078 --> 00:54:16,580
Come, good Christian.

981
00:54:19,583 --> 00:54:22,085
[CHRISTIAN SHOUTS]

982
00:54:31,970 --> 00:54:33,096
Come.

983
00:54:33,096 --> 00:54:34,764
Now, now, good Christian.

984
00:54:34,764 --> 00:54:36,099
You've shown great courage.

985
00:54:43,565 --> 00:54:46,443
You have passed a
trial of your faith.

986
00:54:46,443 --> 00:54:46,985
Barely.

987
00:54:46,985 --> 00:54:50,822
But, well, my
name is Watchful,

988
00:54:50,822 --> 00:54:53,325
and this is my
home, and yours.

989
00:54:54,618 --> 00:54:56,578
My heart is still pounding.

990
00:54:56,578 --> 00:55:00,582
I fear I have almost
lost my newfound joy.

991
00:55:00,582 --> 00:55:04,127
Well, you'd have to be
dead not to feel some fear.

992
00:55:04,127 --> 00:55:06,838
Do not let that perturb you.

993
00:55:06,838 --> 00:55:11,468
Now you are here with
me and my daughters,

994
00:55:11,468 --> 00:55:18,266
Discretion, Prudence,
Piety, and sweet Charity.

995
00:55:18,266 --> 00:55:21,310
We welcome you to our
family, good Christian.

996
00:55:21,310 --> 00:55:22,854
Thank you.

997
00:55:22,854 --> 00:55:25,440
Thank you for
your hospitality.

998
00:55:25,440 --> 00:55:28,568
I've never seen
anything like this.

999
00:55:28,568 --> 00:55:31,821
The King of the Celestial
City built this house

1000
00:55:31,821 --> 00:55:35,700
for the purpose of refreshing
pilgrims such as yourself.

1001
00:55:35,700 --> 00:55:39,621
It is now your house
as well as ours.

1002
00:55:39,621 --> 00:55:43,124
Others have taken the same
path you now journey on.

1003
00:55:43,124 --> 00:55:46,210
Let their example be an
encouragement to you,

1004
00:55:46,210 --> 00:55:49,255
for you are now part of
their glorious company.

1005
00:55:49,255 --> 00:55:52,592
You no longer walk alone.

1006
00:55:52,592 --> 00:55:53,968
Now, please.

1007
00:55:53,968 --> 00:55:55,387
Come to the table.

1008
00:55:55,387 --> 00:55:58,765
[GENTLE MUSIC]

1009
00:56:06,981 --> 00:56:10,359
And that's what set
me on this path.

1010
00:56:10,359 --> 00:56:13,572
But I must say that every step
has taught me something new,

1011
00:56:13,572 --> 00:56:17,325
and every hardship
strengthened me.

1012
00:56:17,325 --> 00:56:20,870
I have learned that the
King wastes nothing.

1013
00:56:20,870 --> 00:56:24,708
And, well, here I am,
still in one piece.

1014
00:56:24,708 --> 00:56:26,710
[LAUGHTER]

1015
00:56:28,002 --> 00:56:30,880
And your family?

1016
00:56:30,880 --> 00:56:32,632
[SIGH]

1017
00:56:32,632 --> 00:56:33,842
Sister.

1018
00:56:33,842 --> 00:56:39,723
I only ask because I
see them in your heart.

1019
00:56:39,723 --> 00:56:43,477
It is my one regret.

1020
00:56:43,477 --> 00:56:46,813
I wish I had been better
at convincing them.

1021
00:56:46,813 --> 00:56:50,859
There is no need to hide your
tears here, dear Christian.

1022
00:56:50,859 --> 00:56:52,861
You are among family.

1023
00:56:52,861 --> 00:56:58,199
I love my wife, and I
love my children dearly.

1024
00:56:58,199 --> 00:57:00,702
It does me good
to speak of them

1025
00:57:00,702 --> 00:57:03,872
since I carry them
in my heart,

1026
00:57:03,872 --> 00:57:06,249
holding on to
the King's promise

1027
00:57:06,249 --> 00:57:10,211
that they, too, may
understand and follow

1028
00:57:10,211 --> 00:57:15,258
or that I might have peace
if they choose not to.

1029
00:57:15,258 --> 00:57:16,593
Be assured.

1030
00:57:16,593 --> 00:57:19,721
The King is aware
of your sorrow.

1031
00:57:19,721 --> 00:57:24,893
And not one tear shed
for them is lost.

1032
00:57:24,893 --> 00:57:28,062
Be at peace, good Christian,
and lay your burdens

1033
00:57:28,062 --> 00:57:33,067
at the feet of your King,
for not one hair of your head

1034
00:57:33,067 --> 00:57:35,361
falls without Him knowing.

1035
00:57:35,361 --> 00:57:36,320
Now, come.

1036
00:57:36,320 --> 00:57:39,073
There is a special
place for you tonight

1037
00:57:39,073 --> 00:57:44,370
to rest your weary head,
your heart, and your soul.

1038
00:57:54,213 --> 00:57:55,965
I think it suits him.

1039
00:57:55,965 --> 00:57:57,258
Of course.

1040
00:57:57,258 --> 00:58:00,845
He's fitted for a purpose.

1041
00:58:00,845 --> 00:58:04,348
It's not as comfortable
as my other clothes.

1042
00:58:04,348 --> 00:58:08,562
But more in keeping with the
next stage of your journey.

1043
00:58:08,562 --> 00:58:10,438
Now, let's accompany him to--

1044
00:58:10,438 --> 00:58:13,817
Oh, no need to
bother yourself-- oh!

1045
00:58:13,817 --> 00:58:15,694
Oh, dear.

1046
00:58:15,694 --> 00:58:17,862
Oh, my.

1047
00:58:17,862 --> 00:58:18,572
I'm fine.

1048
00:58:21,866 --> 00:58:24,077
I guess it's just as
dangerous going down

1049
00:58:24,077 --> 00:58:25,203
a hill than climbing up.

1050
00:58:27,747 --> 00:58:28,707
[SHOUT]

1051
00:58:31,084 --> 00:58:33,461
It is difficult for
anyone to go down

1052
00:58:33,461 --> 00:58:35,714
to the Valley of Humiliation.

1053
00:58:35,714 --> 00:58:40,719
And when they do,
they must walk alone.

1054
00:58:40,719 --> 00:58:41,219
The what?

1055
00:58:43,847 --> 00:58:48,226
It sounded like you
said the Valley of--

1056
00:58:48,226 --> 00:58:49,185
[GASPS]

1057
00:58:49,185 --> 00:58:52,856
[FOREBODING MUSIC]

1058
00:58:52,856 --> 00:58:53,565
What is this?

1059
00:58:59,362 --> 00:59:00,697
Where am I?

1060
00:59:05,201 --> 00:59:11,374
So, a sword, a shield, armor.

1061
00:59:14,377 --> 00:59:16,004
They were preparing
me for battle.

1062
00:59:20,258 --> 00:59:23,720
[HEAVY MUSIC]

1063
00:59:33,605 --> 00:59:35,106
Courage.

1064
00:59:35,106 --> 00:59:36,190
Courage!

1065
00:59:43,072 --> 00:59:44,824
Why, Christian.

1066
00:59:44,824 --> 00:59:48,620
What are you doing here
in this horrid place

1067
00:59:48,620 --> 00:59:51,706
so far away from
your comfortable home

1068
00:59:51,706 --> 00:59:54,626
and loving family?

1069
00:59:54,626 --> 00:59:55,835
Who are you?

1070
00:59:55,835 --> 00:59:57,754
You don't recognize me?

1071
00:59:57,754 --> 01:00:03,342
[LAUGHS] Why, I
am your prince.

1072
01:00:03,342 --> 01:00:06,387
My prince?

1073
01:00:06,387 --> 01:00:08,222
Now, really.

1074
01:00:08,222 --> 01:00:09,891
A sword.

1075
01:00:09,891 --> 01:00:13,436
As you can see, I am unarmed.

1076
01:00:13,436 --> 01:00:16,189
Now, let's go back.

1077
01:00:16,189 --> 01:00:17,065
Back?

1078
01:00:17,065 --> 01:00:19,192
Christiana and the boys.

1079
01:00:19,192 --> 01:00:21,569
You have no idea how
much they miss you.

1080
01:00:21,569 --> 01:00:22,570
Father, come home.

1081
01:00:22,570 --> 01:00:23,947
Come home.

1082
01:00:23,947 --> 01:00:26,324
If you'd only return.

1083
01:00:26,324 --> 01:00:29,368
You miss them, don't you?

1084
01:00:29,368 --> 01:00:30,203
I do.

1085
01:00:30,203 --> 01:00:31,370
Father, where are you?

1086
01:00:31,370 --> 01:00:32,580
Come home.

1087
01:00:32,580 --> 01:00:34,708
Oh, Christian, why?

1088
01:00:34,708 --> 01:00:38,962
But I am on this
journey for the King,

1089
01:00:38,962 --> 01:00:40,964
and I will not be dissuaded.

1090
01:00:40,964 --> 01:00:42,757
So noble.

1091
01:00:42,757 --> 01:00:46,094
Believe me, no one
admires you more

1092
01:00:46,094 --> 01:00:49,513
than I. But think about it.

1093
01:00:49,513 --> 01:00:52,391
Even if you reach
your destination, what

1094
01:00:52,391 --> 01:00:55,103
will become of those you love?

1095
01:00:55,103 --> 01:00:57,605
Perhaps you'll save yourself.

1096
01:00:57,605 --> 01:01:03,319
But what of them?

1097
01:01:03,319 --> 01:01:04,570
No.

1098
01:01:04,570 --> 01:01:06,948
I think it's best
you return with me.

1099
01:01:10,368 --> 01:01:11,619
Now...

1100
01:01:12,829 --> 01:01:14,956
[EERIE MUSIC]

1101
01:01:15,957 --> 01:01:18,376
Put down your sword.

1102
01:01:18,376 --> 01:01:20,586
[TENSE MUSIC]

1103
01:01:23,089 --> 01:01:26,843
And their gaze is to the
things which last forever.

1104
01:01:26,843 --> 01:01:29,595
Keep this in mind,
Christian, for you

1105
01:01:29,595 --> 01:01:31,597
will meet people
who will pretend

1106
01:01:31,597 --> 01:01:37,686
to lead you in the right and
will only lead you into--

1107
01:01:37,686 --> 01:01:38,855
Misery.

1108
01:01:40,314 --> 01:01:41,733
What?

1109
01:01:41,733 --> 01:01:45,486
The King has never failed me.

1110
01:01:45,486 --> 01:01:49,615
And I will not fail
Him, you deceiver,

1111
01:01:49,615 --> 01:01:52,744
you liar, you usurper
of all that is good--

1112
01:01:52,744 --> 01:01:53,244
Silence.

1113
01:01:53,244 --> 01:01:54,078
--and true.

1114
01:01:54,078 --> 01:01:57,081
I served under you and
found nothing but misery.

1115
01:01:57,081 --> 01:01:58,082
Silence!

1116
01:01:58,082 --> 01:02:01,210
My allegiance is with
the Celestial King.

1117
01:02:01,210 --> 01:02:02,211
Is it?

1118
01:02:02,211 --> 01:02:03,337
You heard me.

1119
01:02:03,337 --> 01:02:04,130
How many times

1120
01:02:04,130 --> 01:02:06,590
have you already failed
Him on this journey?

1121
01:02:06,590 --> 01:02:09,343
You are a disgrace to
this King of yours.

1122
01:02:09,343 --> 01:02:13,222
Which makes His mercy and
forgiveness the sweeter.

1123
01:02:13,222 --> 01:02:16,225
You are a deceiver that
binds your subjects

1124
01:02:16,225 --> 01:02:18,352
with invisible chains.

1125
01:02:18,352 --> 01:02:22,565
The King has broken
mine, and I am free.

1126
01:02:22,565 --> 01:02:23,817
I follow Him.

1127
01:02:23,817 --> 01:02:26,235
Then prepare to
forfeit your journey,

1128
01:02:26,235 --> 01:02:31,449
for I swear you
will go no further.

1129
01:02:31,449 --> 01:02:34,953
[TENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

1130
01:02:48,883 --> 01:02:50,384
[CHRISTIAN SHOUTS]

1131
01:02:51,385 --> 01:02:53,137
[MASTER GROWLS]

1132
01:03:20,331 --> 01:03:22,333
[GROWLING]

1133
01:03:22,333 --> 01:03:23,376
[CHRISTIAN SHOUTS]

1134
01:04:29,943 --> 01:04:33,446
[OMINOUS ETHEREAL MUSIC]

1135
01:04:35,448 --> 01:04:37,951
You're mine!

1136
01:04:37,951 --> 01:04:41,454
Do not gloat over
me, you fiend.

1137
01:04:41,454 --> 01:04:47,876
Though I have fallen,
I will yet arise!

1138
01:04:47,876 --> 01:04:51,380
[INTENSE DRAMATIC MUSIC]

1139
01:04:59,597 --> 01:05:02,976
You will see me
again, Christian,

1140
01:05:02,976 --> 01:05:07,063
when the waves overpower
you, when death's cold arms

1141
01:05:07,063 --> 01:05:11,943
wrap themselves around
your wretched soul,

1142
01:05:11,943 --> 01:05:14,862
I will be there!

1143
01:05:14,862 --> 01:05:17,865
[SCREAMS] Be gone!

1144
01:05:17,865 --> 01:05:21,827
Be-- be gone.

1145
01:05:27,333 --> 01:05:30,836
[SOFT MUSIC]

1146
01:05:40,221 --> 01:05:41,222
[GASP]

1147
01:05:44,725 --> 01:05:47,561
Faithful?

1148
01:05:47,561 --> 01:05:48,937
And you are?

1149
01:05:52,566 --> 01:05:55,069
And so you found the Book.

1150
01:05:55,069 --> 01:05:57,821
By them, I learned
about the coming war,

1151
01:05:57,821 --> 01:05:59,323
the origins of our city.

1152
01:05:59,323 --> 01:06:02,951
A cursed city, a city so
opposite in nature to the one

1153
01:06:02,951 --> 01:06:04,828
you and I journey to.

1154
01:06:04,828 --> 01:06:05,997
One that will last--

1155
01:06:05,997 --> 01:06:07,373
Forever.

1156
01:06:07,373 --> 01:06:08,874
Evangelist.

1157
01:06:08,874 --> 01:06:10,334
[LAUGHTER]

1158
01:06:10,334 --> 01:06:12,086
It's good to see
you, Christian.

1159
01:06:12,086 --> 01:06:14,338
This is the man who
showed me the way.

1160
01:06:14,338 --> 01:06:17,716
And a treasure he is to
me as well, for I also

1161
01:06:17,716 --> 01:06:19,760
am indebted to him.

1162
01:06:19,760 --> 01:06:21,095
But tell us.

1163
01:06:21,095 --> 01:06:22,721
What brings you this way?

1164
01:06:22,721 --> 01:06:25,016
The joy of your company.

1165
01:06:25,016 --> 01:06:28,186
Now, how about some food?

1166
01:06:28,186 --> 01:06:29,062
Ha.

1167
01:06:29,062 --> 01:06:29,853
A double blessing.

1168
01:06:29,853 --> 01:06:33,357
Oh, and it could not have
come at a better time.

1169
01:06:33,357 --> 01:06:34,358
[EVANGELIST LAUGHS]

1170
01:06:34,358 --> 01:06:36,610
Come then, friends,
and rest awhile.

1171
01:06:42,200 --> 01:06:43,451
I am glad

1172
01:06:43,451 --> 01:06:46,454
not that you have had to
face so many challenges,

1173
01:06:46,454 --> 01:06:48,581
but that you faced
them with such faith

1174
01:06:48,581 --> 01:06:50,333
and continued in the way.

1175
01:06:50,333 --> 01:06:54,212
A crown, dear Christian and
Faithful, awaits you both,

1176
01:06:54,212 --> 01:06:56,589
and it will last forever.

1177
01:06:56,589 --> 01:06:59,467
But be advised, my friends,
that you are not yet

1178
01:06:59,467 --> 01:07:01,635
out of the reach of evil.

1179
01:07:01,635 --> 01:07:03,096
And--

1180
01:07:03,096 --> 01:07:03,596
And?

1181
01:07:03,596 --> 01:07:07,100
[SOMBER MUSIC]

1182
01:07:10,561 --> 01:07:13,689
What more do you
have to tell us?

1183
01:07:13,689 --> 01:07:15,816
You--

1184
01:07:15,816 --> 01:07:18,319
You didn't just come
here to sip tea.

1185
01:07:18,319 --> 01:07:20,446
There's more, is there not?

1186
01:07:20,446 --> 01:07:24,575
You cannot expect to
continue without hardships.

1187
01:07:24,575 --> 01:07:28,829
But we've already proven
ourselves capable of that.

1188
01:07:28,829 --> 01:07:30,498
And we have the
dents to prove it.

1189
01:07:30,498 --> 01:07:31,874
[CHRISTIAN LAUGHS]

1190
01:07:31,874 --> 01:07:33,459
No.

1191
01:07:33,459 --> 01:07:36,754
I mean severe, more
difficult hardships,

1192
01:07:36,754 --> 01:07:39,965
hardships from which
you might not escape.

1193
01:07:39,965 --> 01:07:42,093
Meaning?

1194
01:07:42,093 --> 01:07:48,015
You will soon come to a town
where you will be arrested.

1195
01:07:48,015 --> 01:07:48,516
Arrested?

1196
01:07:51,102 --> 01:07:54,688
And one or both of you

1197
01:07:54,688 --> 01:07:58,066
will seal your
testimony with blood.

1198
01:07:58,859 --> 01:08:02,696
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

1199
01:08:02,696 --> 01:08:06,117
The town you will go
through is unique.

1200
01:08:06,117 --> 01:08:10,496
Welcome to Vanity Fair.

1201
01:08:10,496 --> 01:08:15,459
It was constructed by the evil
Apollyon on the very path that

1202
01:08:15,459 --> 01:08:17,461
leads to the Celestial City.

1203
01:08:17,461 --> 01:08:18,962
A pie, I say.

1204
01:08:18,962 --> 01:08:22,841
The town hosts a
fair that never ends.

1205
01:08:22,841 --> 01:08:26,220
[LIGHT PLAYFUL MUSIC]

1206
01:08:26,220 --> 01:08:28,096
[CHATTER]

1207
01:08:30,015 --> 01:08:32,601
And in it, you will
encounter everything

1208
01:08:32,601 --> 01:08:34,562
that tempts a human heart.

1209
01:08:34,562 --> 01:08:35,854
Look, Fortunata.

1210
01:08:35,854 --> 01:08:38,607
I've never laid eyes
on these before.

1211
01:08:38,607 --> 01:08:41,319
Through this town,
you must go.

1212
01:08:41,319 --> 01:08:42,736
Come now, strangers!

1213
01:08:42,736 --> 01:08:44,238
Try our spirits!

1214
01:08:44,238 --> 01:08:45,739
But be warned.

1215
01:08:45,739 --> 01:08:49,743
Do not be overly confident,
and heed to this warning.

1216
01:08:49,743 --> 01:08:52,455
Settle it in your
heart what you will

1217
01:08:52,455 --> 01:08:55,333
do before you enter
the town, for many

1218
01:08:55,333 --> 01:08:59,462
have fallen who walked in
with one eye on eternity

1219
01:08:59,462 --> 01:09:01,464
and the other on the present.

1220
01:09:01,464 --> 01:09:03,882
I would keep my
eye on those two.

1221
01:09:03,882 --> 01:09:06,219
--and, well, just about
anything you like.

1222
01:09:06,219 --> 01:09:07,220
Or the vests.

1223
01:09:07,220 --> 01:09:08,596
Have you seen the vests?

1224
01:09:08,596 --> 01:09:11,014
You can't be here
without playing a game.

1225
01:09:11,014 --> 01:09:11,515
No!

1226
01:09:18,939 --> 01:09:19,857
[GASP]

1227
01:09:20,358 --> 01:09:22,860
No?

1228
01:09:22,860 --> 01:09:27,365
What we wish to obtain,
you do not sell here.

1229
01:09:27,365 --> 01:09:30,075
That, sir, is impossible.

1230
01:09:30,075 --> 01:09:32,620
Did you hear what he said?

1231
01:09:32,620 --> 01:09:34,705
What is going on here?

1232
01:09:34,705 --> 01:09:36,749
What is the meaning
of this disruption?

1233
01:09:36,749 --> 01:09:41,587
These strange strangers
insist that what they need

1234
01:09:41,587 --> 01:09:43,464
is not available here.

1235
01:09:43,464 --> 01:09:47,968
And as a result, they
have disrupted our fair.

1236
01:09:47,968 --> 01:09:49,262
Well, then, to the Judge.

1237
01:09:49,262 --> 01:09:50,721
Out of my way.

1238
01:09:50,721 --> 01:09:51,597
What?

1239
01:09:51,597 --> 01:09:55,268
But we have done nothing.

1240
01:09:55,268 --> 01:09:56,685
Excuse me.

1241
01:09:56,685 --> 01:09:57,185
Make way.

1242
01:09:57,185 --> 01:09:57,686
Make way.

1243
01:09:57,686 --> 01:09:58,186
Yes.

1244
01:09:58,186 --> 01:09:59,187
Make way, I say.

1245
01:09:59,187 --> 01:10:02,107
[LIGHT PLAYFUL MUSIC]

1246
01:10:02,107 --> 01:10:03,609
This is preposterous.

1247
01:10:09,072 --> 01:10:10,491
Put the scoundrels away.

1248
01:10:14,370 --> 01:10:16,204
What is the meaning of this?

1249
01:10:16,204 --> 01:10:18,624
What is this
interruption to our fair?

1250
01:10:18,624 --> 01:10:19,583
What?

1251
01:10:19,583 --> 01:10:23,629
These strange strangers.

1252
01:10:23,629 --> 01:10:25,339
What did they do?

1253
01:10:25,339 --> 01:10:26,715
Nothing.

1254
01:10:26,715 --> 01:10:27,466
Nothing.

1255
01:10:27,466 --> 01:10:28,342
Nothing?

1256
01:10:28,342 --> 01:10:29,718
Exactly.

1257
01:10:29,718 --> 01:10:31,595
They won't take
part in anything.

1258
01:10:31,595 --> 01:10:33,597
They won't buy anything.

1259
01:10:33,597 --> 01:10:36,517
They are doing nothing.

1260
01:10:36,517 --> 01:10:40,354
Well, by doing nothing, you
have interrupted our fair.

1261
01:10:40,354 --> 01:10:42,315
There's only one thing to do.

1262
01:10:42,315 --> 01:10:44,442
Call the jury.

1263
01:10:44,442 --> 01:10:45,568
Jury!

1264
01:10:45,568 --> 01:10:47,570
[WHIRRING]

1265
01:10:48,571 --> 01:10:49,572
[BELL DINGS]

1266
01:10:50,573 --> 01:10:52,074
All present.

1267
01:10:52,074 --> 01:10:52,866
Right.

1268
01:10:52,866 --> 01:10:54,993
Do we have the witnesses?

1269
01:10:54,993 --> 01:10:58,581
Envy and Gain Glory.

1270
01:10:58,581 --> 01:11:01,334
Do you know these prisoners?

1271
01:11:01,334 --> 01:11:04,878
Yes, at least 15 minutes.

1272
01:11:04,878 --> 01:11:07,130
And what do you
hold against them?

1273
01:11:07,130 --> 01:11:11,218
They said that what they
wanted we did not have.

1274
01:11:11,218 --> 01:11:15,138
And what could
that possibly be?

1275
01:11:15,138 --> 01:11:20,060
Peace, joy,
love, unselfishness,

1276
01:11:20,060 --> 01:11:22,813
patience, contentment.

1277
01:11:22,813 --> 01:11:26,817
And a crown that never fades
away, among other things.

1278
01:11:26,817 --> 01:11:27,943
Do we sell that?

1279
01:11:27,943 --> 01:11:30,321
[ALL CHATTERING]

1280
01:11:32,698 --> 01:11:34,074
Quiet in the court.

1281
01:11:34,074 --> 01:11:37,870
Quiet in the court!

1282
01:11:37,870 --> 01:11:40,080
Come, come.

1283
01:11:40,080 --> 01:11:43,083
Do we sell any
of these things?

1284
01:11:43,083 --> 01:11:44,460
Of course not.

1285
01:11:44,460 --> 01:11:47,463
This is Vanity Fair,
not La La Land.

1286
01:11:47,463 --> 01:11:51,216
I wouldn't even know where
to get those kinds of things.

1287
01:11:51,216 --> 01:11:55,220
Well, I have been informed
that such things as you speak

1288
01:11:55,220 --> 01:11:59,475
of cannot be sold, else
you would find it aplenty

1289
01:11:59,475 --> 01:12:01,685
in our fabulous fair.

1290
01:12:01,685 --> 01:12:04,980
And that you say truthfully,
for they can only

1291
01:12:04,980 --> 01:12:07,358
be obtained by the
King who gives them

1292
01:12:07,358 --> 01:12:09,443
to all who desire them.

1293
01:12:09,443 --> 01:12:12,821
Though they come not at
the price of any coin,

1294
01:12:12,821 --> 01:12:16,700
but of the surrender of the
heart to His better ways.

1295
01:12:16,700 --> 01:12:17,368
[COUGHS]

1296
01:12:18,326 --> 01:12:23,707
You have proof that these
wonderful things even exist?

1297
01:12:23,707 --> 01:12:26,209
By the King's grace.

1298
01:12:26,209 --> 01:12:28,712
Well, then, show them to us.

1299
01:12:28,712 --> 01:12:32,090
They are not such things as
you can hold in your hand.

1300
01:12:32,090 --> 01:12:35,969
But are most excellent things
which are held in the heart

1301
01:12:35,969 --> 01:12:39,222
and are the most valuable
during hardships,

1302
01:12:39,222 --> 01:12:43,436
for it is then that their
worth is most evident.

1303
01:12:43,436 --> 01:12:46,855
Well, then, may I suggest
just that, my lord,

1304
01:12:46,855 --> 01:12:50,568
that we may see what we
are so missing out on?

1305
01:12:50,568 --> 01:12:51,860
Suggest what?

1306
01:12:51,860 --> 01:12:54,572
Why, hardships, of course.

1307
01:12:54,572 --> 01:12:56,323
Hardships?

1308
01:12:56,323 --> 01:12:57,324
Hardships.

1309
01:12:57,324 --> 01:12:59,577
Cruelty, approach the bench.

1310
01:13:02,705 --> 01:13:04,457
What are you thinking?

1311
01:13:04,457 --> 01:13:06,333
The fair has been disrupted.

1312
01:13:06,333 --> 01:13:08,210
Is that not cause enough?

1313
01:13:08,210 --> 01:13:09,878
I am ready for judgment.

1314
01:13:09,878 --> 01:13:12,130
But not the townspeople.

1315
01:13:12,130 --> 01:13:13,966
What are you talking about?

1316
01:13:13,966 --> 01:13:15,092
Did you not see

1317
01:13:15,092 --> 01:13:17,970
how they reacted to the
comments of these two men?

1318
01:13:17,970 --> 01:13:20,723
I say punish them
harshly and openly

1319
01:13:20,723 --> 01:13:23,642
that our people have evidence
that these two fools possess

1320
01:13:23,642 --> 01:13:27,688
nothing of this-- this
peace, love, unselfishness,

1321
01:13:27,688 --> 01:13:30,441
and blah-blah that
they so boast about.

1322
01:13:30,441 --> 01:13:31,942
And therefore, that
our townspeople

1323
01:13:31,942 --> 01:13:34,445
are not missing out
on anything at all.

1324
01:13:34,445 --> 01:13:36,363
Oh, I see.

1325
01:13:36,363 --> 01:13:37,740
I do, indeed.

1326
01:13:37,740 --> 01:13:39,950
Very well, then.

1327
01:13:39,950 --> 01:13:42,620
I will postpone my
judgment until evidence

1328
01:13:42,620 --> 01:13:44,246
has been submitted.

1329
01:13:44,246 --> 01:13:48,709
Commence the hardship,
and resume the fair.

1330
01:13:48,709 --> 01:13:50,210
What are you doing?

1331
01:13:50,210 --> 01:13:52,212
Unhand me.

1332
01:13:52,212 --> 01:13:53,213
Well, that's over.

1333
01:13:53,213 --> 01:13:55,716
Let's get back to some fun.

1334
01:13:55,716 --> 01:13:58,135
[LIGHT PLAYFUL MUSIC]

1335
01:13:58,135 --> 01:13:59,637
And away we go.

1336
01:13:59,637 --> 01:14:02,097
[LAUGHTER, CHATTER]

1337
01:14:11,565 --> 01:14:14,485
So you got something
better than us.

1338
01:14:14,485 --> 01:14:16,945
Right in the head.

1339
01:14:16,945 --> 01:14:18,947
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1340
01:14:20,949 --> 01:14:24,452
This is better than the fair.

1341
01:14:24,452 --> 01:14:25,370
Need more rocks.

1342
01:14:31,376 --> 01:14:33,712
[LAUGHS] Look at them now.

1343
01:14:38,341 --> 01:14:39,593
They what?

1344
01:14:39,593 --> 01:14:43,514
Took every blow, every
rock, every insult.

1345
01:14:43,514 --> 01:14:46,725
And not once did
they retaliate?

1346
01:14:46,725 --> 01:14:50,478
They even tried to smile
back at their attackers.

1347
01:14:50,478 --> 01:14:51,438
No.

1348
01:14:51,438 --> 01:14:53,190
How vile!

1349
01:14:53,190 --> 01:14:55,568
How very unnatural of them.

1350
01:14:55,568 --> 01:14:58,111
How purely evil.

1351
01:14:58,111 --> 01:15:01,574
I say the sooner we get
rid of them, the better.

1352
01:15:01,574 --> 01:15:03,617
It's unanimous.

1353
01:15:03,617 --> 01:15:04,952
Bring in the prisoners.

1354
01:15:04,952 --> 01:15:07,079
[CROWD SHOUTING]

1355
01:15:08,872 --> 01:15:11,584
The evidence was not
to our satisfaction.

1356
01:15:11,584 --> 01:15:13,335
Our behavior was in
keeping with our--

1357
01:15:13,335 --> 01:15:13,836
Order!

1358
01:15:13,836 --> 01:15:16,213
[HEAVY OMINOUS MUSIC]

1359
01:15:16,213 --> 01:15:19,091
I sentence you to death.

1360
01:15:19,091 --> 01:15:20,593
What?

1361
01:15:20,593 --> 01:15:22,469
Starting with him.

1362
01:15:22,469 --> 01:15:23,721
You can't.

1363
01:15:23,721 --> 01:15:24,847
Well, I just did.

1364
01:15:24,847 --> 01:15:25,472
No!

1365
01:15:25,472 --> 01:15:26,599
All right, everyone.

1366
01:15:26,599 --> 01:15:27,766
Back to the fair.

1367
01:15:27,766 --> 01:15:28,851
Faithful.

1368
01:15:28,851 --> 01:15:29,643
Faithful!

1369
01:15:29,643 --> 01:15:31,687
Do not worry, my dear brother.

1370
01:15:31,687 --> 01:15:34,732
This is what Evangelist
came to prepare us for.

1371
01:15:34,732 --> 01:15:38,944
Today, I seal my
testimony with my blood.

1372
01:15:38,944 --> 01:15:40,070
Faithful.

1373
01:15:40,070 --> 01:15:41,321
No!

1374
01:15:41,321 --> 01:15:45,200
Do not weep that I am sent
ahead of you, dear brother.

1375
01:15:45,200 --> 01:15:48,579
Stay true, and I
shall yet see you.

1376
01:15:48,579 --> 01:15:49,079
No!

1377
01:15:49,079 --> 01:15:52,374
I shall yet see you!

1378
01:15:52,374 --> 01:15:53,375
Don't worry.

1379
01:15:53,375 --> 01:15:55,878
You'll have your
turn tomorrow.

1380
01:15:55,878 --> 01:15:57,212
Put him away.

1381
01:15:57,212 --> 01:15:58,714
Faithful.

1382
01:15:58,714 --> 01:16:00,716
Faithful!

1383
01:16:00,716 --> 01:16:04,136
[HEAVY SOMBER MUSIC]

1384
01:16:06,639 --> 01:16:09,099
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

1385
01:16:16,982 --> 01:16:19,317
Oh, Faithful.

1386
01:16:19,317 --> 01:16:20,694
My dear brother, Faithful.

1387
01:16:26,074 --> 01:16:29,703
