that's for certain.

1626
01:29:53,965 --> 01:29:56,092
[BOTH LAUGH]

1627
01:30:00,346 --> 01:30:01,973
What happened?

1628
01:30:01,973 --> 01:30:02,849
I have no idea.

1629
01:30:05,392 --> 01:30:08,563
The path seems to
have vanished.

1630
01:30:08,563 --> 01:30:12,108
And yet you will
still be guided.

1631
01:30:12,108 --> 01:30:15,695
Welcome to the King's
Delightful Mountains,

1632
01:30:15,695 --> 01:30:17,113
a taste of things to come.

1633
01:30:17,113 --> 01:30:18,197
[SHEEP BLEATS]

1634
01:30:18,865 --> 01:30:21,451
Thank you, kind Shepherd.

1635
01:30:21,451 --> 01:30:22,577
My name is--

1636
01:30:22,577 --> 01:30:23,953
Christian.

1637
01:30:23,953 --> 01:30:26,205
And you are Hopeful.

1638
01:30:26,205 --> 01:30:28,708
You are known and loved.

1639
01:30:28,708 --> 01:30:29,626
Tell me.

1640
01:30:29,626 --> 01:30:31,586
Do we know you?

1641
01:30:31,586 --> 01:30:32,837
In part.

1642
01:30:32,837 --> 01:30:35,882
You will be delighted to hear
that you are within sight

1643
01:30:35,882 --> 01:30:40,219
of that city which you
have so diligently sought

1644
01:30:40,219 --> 01:30:43,097
and for which you
have also suffered.

1645
01:30:43,097 --> 01:30:45,725
That is, indeed, good news.

1646
01:30:45,725 --> 01:30:49,979
And the rest of the way,
is it very dangerous?

1647
01:30:49,979 --> 01:30:53,190
Let this knowledge
suffice for now--

1648
01:30:53,190 --> 01:30:57,444
that you do not walk
alone, for the King guides

1649
01:30:57,444 --> 01:31:00,197
you as a shepherd
does his sheep.

1650
01:31:03,367 --> 01:31:09,081
He always goes before, even
if out of sight of the sheep.

1651
01:31:09,081 --> 01:31:13,210
I give you a map for the
rest of your journey.

1652
01:31:13,210 --> 01:31:15,880
Beware the Flatterer.

1653
01:31:15,880 --> 01:31:19,884
Do not sleep on the
enchanted ground.

1654
01:31:19,884 --> 01:31:24,889
Keep the light of the
city ever before you.

1655
01:31:24,889 --> 01:31:27,349
We shall do as you
say, kind Shepherd.

1656
01:31:27,349 --> 01:31:32,063
Now, if you please, is
this the way that leads--

1657
01:31:32,063 --> 01:31:35,066
where did He go?

1658
01:31:35,066 --> 01:31:37,068
He spoke about a map.

1659
01:31:37,068 --> 01:31:38,235
Did you give it to you?

1660
01:31:38,235 --> 01:31:41,197
I was going to ask
you the same thing.

1661
01:31:41,197 --> 01:31:44,951
Alas, it could have come
in handy just about now.

1662
01:31:44,951 --> 01:31:46,828
I don't know what
direction to take.

1663
01:31:46,828 --> 01:31:49,831
Well, isn't this a sight?

1664
01:31:49,831 --> 01:31:52,458
I daresay it's not
every day that one finds

1665
01:31:52,458 --> 01:31:54,877
other pilgrims this far along.

1666
01:31:54,877 --> 01:32:00,717
I-- well, I'm just beside
myself with joy to meet you.

1667
01:32:00,717 --> 01:32:03,970
I'm Christian, and this is
my good friend, Hopeful.

1668
01:32:03,970 --> 01:32:05,638
Such names.

1669
01:32:05,638 --> 01:32:09,475
They can only reflect your
goodly character, I'm sure.

1670
01:32:09,475 --> 01:32:13,062
You're going to the
Celestial City, I suppose?

1671
01:32:13,062 --> 01:32:15,106
Indeed, we are.

1672
01:32:15,106 --> 01:32:17,567
Then we shall walk together.

1673
01:32:17,567 --> 01:32:19,861
But the light of the city
seems to be coming

1674
01:32:19,861 --> 01:32:21,445
from over there.

1675
01:32:21,445 --> 01:32:22,822
Or so it seems.

1676
01:32:22,822 --> 01:32:24,448
Come, come now.

1677
01:32:24,448 --> 01:32:28,119
I know exactly
what I am doing.

1678
01:32:28,119 --> 01:32:30,204
I am a great judge of
character, you know.

1679
01:32:30,204 --> 01:32:34,208
I only accept the company of
those with the same dedicated

1680
01:32:34,208 --> 01:32:36,961
inclinations as I.

1681
01:32:36,961 --> 01:32:41,716
Well, we have tried to
be faithful, though we

1682
01:32:41,716 --> 01:32:44,218
have had our stumblings.

1683
01:32:44,218 --> 01:32:48,723
Christian, however, exceeds
me in both virtue and courage,

1684
01:32:48,723 --> 01:32:53,352
having begun his journey much
earlier than I. I admire him

1685
01:32:53,352 --> 01:32:54,604
completely.

1686
01:32:54,604 --> 01:32:57,356
And upon hearing
that, so do I.

1687
01:32:57,356 --> 01:32:59,316
Oh, come now.

1688
01:32:59,316 --> 01:33:01,694
I'm hardly a model of virtue.

1689
01:33:01,694 --> 01:33:02,569
Tut, tut.

1690
01:33:02,569 --> 01:33:04,446
You are too modest.

1691
01:33:04,446 --> 01:33:06,198
Share with me even a snippet

1692
01:33:06,198 --> 01:33:07,867
of one of your
brave adventures,

1693
01:33:07,867 --> 01:33:10,577
and I shall be
forever in your debt.

1694
01:33:10,577 --> 01:33:13,580
Well, I don't know.

1695
01:33:13,580 --> 01:33:14,456
There are so many.

1696
01:33:14,456 --> 01:33:17,084
Ah, such humility.

1697
01:33:17,084 --> 01:33:19,461
He survived the
Swamp of Despondency.

1698
01:33:19,461 --> 01:33:21,088
That despicable mire.

1699
01:33:21,088 --> 01:33:22,965
And the Valley of Humiliation.

1700
01:33:22,965 --> 01:33:24,717
In which so many
have gone mad.

1701
01:33:24,717 --> 01:33:27,344
We escaped the
Castle of Despair.

1702
01:33:27,344 --> 01:33:29,596
Which so few seem
to have done,

1703
01:33:29,596 --> 01:33:31,390
judging by the bones
scattered there,

1704
01:33:31,390 --> 01:33:33,225
I might add.

1705
01:33:33,225 --> 01:33:35,561
I should fall at your feet.

1706
01:33:35,561 --> 01:33:37,980
Oh, and I fought
Apollyon, you know.

1707
01:33:37,980 --> 01:33:41,358
[GASPS] Well, aren't
you the greatest--

1708
01:33:41,358 --> 01:33:43,861
[HOPEFUL AND CHRISTIAN SHOUT]

1709
01:33:43,861 --> 01:33:45,362
[MAN LAUGHS]

1710
01:33:45,362 --> 01:33:49,366
The greatest fool,
I should say!

1711
01:33:49,366 --> 01:33:50,576
You.

1712
01:33:50,576 --> 01:33:51,577
Surprised?

1713
01:33:51,577 --> 01:33:53,955
Do you think we
give up that easily?

1714
01:33:53,955 --> 01:33:55,456
Get us out of here.

1715
01:33:55,456 --> 01:33:57,333
See these strands?

1716
01:33:57,333 --> 01:33:59,877
They were woven by
your own boasting.

1717
01:33:59,877 --> 01:34:03,464
And judging by them, I fear
your own pride has kept you

1718
01:34:03,464 --> 01:34:05,132
from your destination.

1719
01:34:05,132 --> 01:34:08,094
Let us go.

1720
01:34:08,094 --> 01:34:09,095
[TSKS]

1721
01:34:09,595 --> 01:34:10,888
A pity you will not be able

1722
01:34:10,888 --> 01:34:12,890
to get word to your wife

1723
01:34:12,890 --> 01:34:15,226
or, shall I say, widow.

1724
01:34:15,226 --> 01:34:16,602
[LAUGHS]

1725
01:34:16,602 --> 01:34:19,355
[HEAVY MUSIC]

1726
01:34:19,355 --> 01:34:20,314
No!

1727
01:34:20,314 --> 01:34:22,608
A Flatterer.

1728
01:34:22,608 --> 01:34:23,317
What?

1729
01:34:23,317 --> 01:34:25,444
He was a Flatterer.

1730
01:34:25,444 --> 01:34:28,364
We stepped right
into his trap.

1731
01:34:28,364 --> 01:34:31,325
When am I ever going to learn?

1732
01:34:31,325 --> 01:34:33,244
Let's not despair
again, Christian.

1733
01:34:33,244 --> 01:34:35,204
But now I won't be able--

1734
01:34:35,204 --> 01:34:36,873
Stop, please.

1735
01:34:36,873 --> 01:34:39,083
Let's not give up hope.

1736
01:34:39,083 --> 01:34:42,211
We've got to think back
on what the Shepherd said.

1737
01:34:42,211 --> 01:34:44,255
"Beware of the Flatterer."

1738
01:34:44,255 --> 01:34:46,382
Before that.

1739
01:34:46,382 --> 01:34:48,968
"You do not walk alone."

1740
01:34:48,968 --> 01:34:51,721
[SOFT ETHEREAL MUSIC]

1741
01:34:51,721 --> 01:34:55,224
And you are not alone now.

1742
01:34:55,224 --> 01:34:57,143
[BOTH GRUNT]

1743
01:35:04,358 --> 01:35:06,819
That was painful.

1744
01:35:06,819 --> 01:35:11,073
Sometimes, Hopeful, a
rescue means wounds.

1745
01:35:11,073 --> 01:35:15,119
Did you not meet the Shepherd
of the Delightful Mountains?

1746
01:35:15,119 --> 01:35:17,329
We did.

1747
01:35:17,329 --> 01:35:19,373
And did He not give you a map?

1748
01:35:19,373 --> 01:35:21,125
He only counseled--

1749
01:35:21,125 --> 01:35:22,960
And warned us.

1750
01:35:22,960 --> 01:35:27,131
But the map, He
didn't give us.

1751
01:35:27,131 --> 01:35:31,385
The King's instructions
are a map, Christian.

1752
01:35:31,385 --> 01:35:37,224
Did they not indicate where
to go and where not to go?

1753
01:35:37,224 --> 01:35:39,101
They did.

1754
01:35:39,101 --> 01:35:42,188
I can see that now.

1755
01:35:42,188 --> 01:35:45,942
Be vigilant to your
last breath, for you are

1756
01:35:45,942 --> 01:35:49,445
very near your journey's end.

1757
01:35:49,445 --> 01:35:52,448
How will we know
when we are there?

1758
01:35:52,448 --> 01:35:56,077
When you stand at the
brink of the last shadow,

1759
01:35:56,077 --> 01:36:00,206
the border beyond which
evil has no power, where

1760
01:36:00,206 --> 01:36:05,586
the old is left forever
and newness of life begins.

1761
01:36:05,586 --> 01:36:09,340
Do not fear to cross, for
your eternal city lies beyond.

1762
01:36:12,093 --> 01:36:16,222
You will find your step
deeper or shallower

1763
01:36:16,222 --> 01:36:20,476
as you believe in the
superiority of the King.

1764
01:36:25,356 --> 01:36:26,858
Where are you going?

1765
01:36:26,858 --> 01:36:28,860
Can you not see
the city beyond?

1766
01:36:42,331 --> 01:36:43,833
I'm looking for the crossing.

1767
01:36:52,716 --> 01:36:54,718
Christian.

1768
01:36:54,718 --> 01:36:55,719
Christian.

1769
01:37:00,724 --> 01:37:02,768
I don't understand.

1770
01:37:02,768 --> 01:37:06,063
There doesn't seem to be
any way to get across.

1771
01:37:06,063 --> 01:37:07,564
No way around it.

1772
01:37:07,564 --> 01:37:08,858
No way over it.

1773
01:37:08,858 --> 01:37:11,443
Only through it.

1774
01:37:11,443 --> 01:37:13,320
What are you talking about?

1775
01:37:13,320 --> 01:37:14,071
There's no way--

1776
01:37:14,071 --> 01:37:17,449
Can't you see what this is?

1777
01:37:17,449 --> 01:37:22,246
This is the last shadow,
the borders beyond which

1778
01:37:22,246 --> 01:37:25,707
evil has no power--

1779
01:37:25,707 --> 01:37:28,085
Death.

1780
01:37:28,085 --> 01:37:29,086
Death?

1781
01:37:29,086 --> 01:37:35,092
Where the old is left forever
and newness of life begins.

1782
01:37:35,092 --> 01:37:37,469
We can go forward.

1783
01:37:37,469 --> 01:37:40,389
But we can never go back.

1784
01:37:40,389 --> 01:37:43,850
[SOFT HEAVY MUSIC]

1785
01:37:47,729 --> 01:37:48,689
I'm going.

1786
01:37:48,689 --> 01:37:50,191
Hopeful?

1787
01:37:50,191 --> 01:37:54,361
I am going, Christian.

1788
01:37:54,361 --> 01:37:58,074
And I-- I'm not.

1789
01:37:58,074 --> 01:37:58,865
You have to.

1790
01:37:58,865 --> 01:38:00,326
You've come this far.

1791
01:38:00,326 --> 01:38:03,704
To make a way for
others, Hopeful.

1792
01:38:03,704 --> 01:38:06,082
To make a way from
my wife, my family--

1793
01:38:06,082 --> 01:38:07,874
to save them.

1794
01:38:07,874 --> 01:38:12,129
And that, you cannot do, for
the way has already been paved

1795
01:38:12,129 --> 01:38:16,717
for others by the same
one that paved it for you.

1796
01:38:16,717 --> 01:38:19,136
Your part has been to follow.

1797
01:38:19,136 --> 01:38:22,098
And, believe me, it has
caused no lack of talk

1798
01:38:22,098 --> 01:38:24,850
among the people of
your former city.

1799
01:38:24,850 --> 01:38:28,062
Others will follow.

1800
01:38:28,062 --> 01:38:30,814
Including my wife
and children?

1801
01:38:30,814 --> 01:38:34,443
That question, dear Christian,
can only be answered by them.

1802
01:38:34,443 --> 01:38:38,364
But if they do, would you
lead them to this point only

1803
01:38:38,364 --> 01:38:41,117
or to a new and
everlasting life

1804
01:38:41,117 --> 01:38:45,204
in which evil has no part?

1805
01:38:45,204 --> 01:38:47,081
I'm going.

1806
01:38:48,582 --> 01:38:50,376
I must.

1807
01:38:50,376 --> 01:38:52,211
Hopeful.

1808
01:38:52,211 --> 01:38:54,964
All through our
journey, you told me

1809
01:38:54,964 --> 01:38:58,092
that the King's ways
never failed you,

1810
01:38:58,092 --> 01:39:00,386
that His promises were true.

1811
01:39:00,386 --> 01:39:04,348
I know He will
not fail me now.

1812
01:39:04,348 --> 01:39:05,849
Goodbye, dear brother.

1813
01:39:09,686 --> 01:39:10,187
Hopeful!

1814
01:39:16,360 --> 01:39:18,237
He's gone.

1815
01:39:18,237 --> 01:39:21,198
To the Celestial
City, to all that

1816
01:39:21,198 --> 01:39:26,078
has been promised, to what
you both sought so diligently.

1817
01:39:29,456 --> 01:39:32,126
Well?

1818
01:39:32,126 --> 01:39:34,503
I'm afraid.

1819
01:39:34,503 --> 01:39:36,630
And there is nothing
wrong with that.

1820
01:39:36,630 --> 01:39:40,884
You have trusted the King
with your life, Christian.

1821
01:39:40,884 --> 01:39:45,097
And I, dear friend,

1822
01:39:45,097 --> 01:39:48,517
I shall trust him with my--

1823
01:39:48,517 --> 01:39:51,478
[POWERFUL DRAMATIC MUSIC]

1824
01:39:58,860 --> 01:40:02,364
You will see me
again, Christian,

1825
01:40:02,364 --> 01:40:06,868
when the waves overpower you,
when death's cold arms wrap

1826
01:40:06,868 --> 01:40:10,372
themselves around
your wretched soul.

1827
01:40:13,334 --> 01:40:17,254
I will be there.

1828
01:40:17,254 --> 01:40:17,754
No!

1829
01:40:21,717 --> 01:40:25,637
You will find your step
deeper or shallower

1830
01:40:25,637 --> 01:40:32,103
as you believe in the
superiority of the King.

1831
01:40:32,103 --> 01:40:32,603
Help!

1832
01:40:32,603 --> 01:40:36,107
[HEAVY DRAMATIC MUSIC]

1833
01:40:42,571 --> 01:40:44,573
[GROWL]

1834
01:40:47,576 --> 01:40:49,578
[SCREAM]

1835
01:40:56,085 --> 01:40:58,087
I'm bleeding.

1836
01:40:58,087 --> 01:41:01,590
[ETHEREAL MUSIC]

1837
01:41:17,063 --> 01:41:19,566
[FOOTSTEPS]

1838
01:41:23,069 --> 01:41:25,071
[GASP]

1839
01:41:35,081 --> 01:41:36,082
You.

1840
01:41:36,082 --> 01:41:39,586
[GENTLE MUSIC]

1841
01:41:40,587 --> 01:41:42,088
You're the Shepherd.

1842
01:41:44,841 --> 01:41:45,717
I am.

1843
01:41:49,095 --> 01:41:51,014
I am the Good Shepherd.

1844
01:41:54,393 --> 01:41:56,728
I saw the blood.

1845
01:41:56,728 --> 01:41:58,980
I was bleeding.

1846
01:41:58,980 --> 01:42:03,569
It was not your blood,
Christian, but mine.

1847
01:42:03,569 --> 01:42:09,074
And you needn't worry
any longer about wounds,

1848
01:42:09,074 --> 01:42:11,618
for you have arrived
to the place where

1849
01:42:11,618 --> 01:42:16,832
the old is passed away and
newness of life begins.

1850
01:42:19,710 --> 01:42:22,087
Welcome, Christian.

1851
01:42:22,087 --> 01:42:26,007
Welcome to the Celestial City.

1852
01:42:26,007 --> 01:42:29,470
[BRIGHT POWERFUL MUSIC]

1853
01:42:46,320 --> 01:42:47,321
Haha!

1854
01:42:47,321 --> 01:42:48,739
Welcome, brother!

1855
01:42:48,739 --> 01:42:49,740
Christian!

1856
01:42:49,740 --> 01:42:50,741
Welcome!

1857
01:42:50,741 --> 01:42:53,702
Christian, my dear brother.

1858
01:42:53,702 --> 01:42:55,704
Hopeful?

1859
01:42:55,704 --> 01:42:56,705
Faithful!

1860
01:42:56,705 --> 01:43:00,709
[LAUGHS] My friends!

1861
01:43:00,709 --> 01:43:03,629
My brothers.

1862
01:43:03,629 --> 01:43:08,217
Oh, that my dear
ones could see this,

1863
01:43:08,217 --> 01:43:11,094
that they, too, would come...

1864
01:43:11,094 --> 01:43:14,848
that they, too, would come!

1865
01:43:18,018 --> 01:43:21,730
[LIGHT MUSIC]

1866
01:43:26,192 --> 01:43:29,195
[MUSIC - "BLESSED ASSURANCE"]

1867
01:43:29,195 --> 01:43:32,699
(SINGING) This is my story.

1868
01:43:32,699 --> 01:43:36,202
This is my song.

1869
01:43:36,202 --> 01:43:43,209
Praising my Savior
all the day long.

1870
01:43:43,209 --> 01:43:46,129
This is my story.

1871
01:43:46,129 --> 01:43:49,633
This is my song.

1872
01:43:49,633 --> 01:43:55,138
Praising my Savior
all the day long.

1873
01:44:15,576 --> 01:44:19,079
[GENTLE MUSIC]

1874
01:44:43,687 --> 01:44:49,943
I know this will break your
heart, as it does mine.

1875
01:44:49,943 --> 01:44:51,820
But I am going

1876
01:44:51,820 --> 01:44:56,074
because I have no doubt
the Book speaks truth.

1877
01:44:58,369 --> 01:45:01,455
I have taken a promise
from its pages, which

1878
01:45:01,455 --> 01:45:05,250
I will carry near my heart.

1879
01:45:05,250 --> 01:45:07,753
"Eye has not seen.

1880
01:45:07,753 --> 01:45:10,714
Ear has not heard.

1881
01:45:10,714 --> 01:45:13,842
Neither can anyone imagine
the wonderful things

1882
01:45:13,842 --> 01:45:19,473
the King has prepared
for those that seek Him."

1883
01:45:19,473 --> 01:45:22,225
Christian is alive!

1884
01:45:22,225 --> 01:45:24,269
[POWERFUL MUSIC]

1885
01:45:27,230 --> 01:45:28,189
Boys?

1886
01:45:28,189 --> 01:45:29,358
